name: 2018-10-21 22.47.00 1895067062116945389_museedulouvre.jpg
text: Лувр. Что бы застать Лувр без людей нужно приходить утром до 8-ми. В остальное время сделать кадр без туристов нереально. Снаружи дворцовый комплекс очень красивый и можно просто погулять вокруг, тем более что рядом сады Тюильри. Но сам музей конечно же заслуживает отдельного дня. Мы попали в музей в первое воскресенье месяца, а значит это день открытых дверей и бесплатный вход для всех. К открытию музея очередь из азиатских туристов на оба входа была человек 100)Внутри музея в подвальном помещении выстроены стены египетских пирамид, целая улица. Размах просто поражает. Количество картин, скульптур и прочих экспонатов огромное. Жаль у нас было мало времени все рассмотреть. Но Мона Лизу увидели)#paris #france🇫🇷 #travel #museedulouvre #monalisa

name: 2019-06-20 13.27.58 2070181427941905850_museedulouvre.jpg
text: Jupiter de Versailles -_Consider following...🙋🏻‍♂️📸🙆‍♂️❤🤦‍♂️✌💁‍♂️for more great pics! Grazie!!__"Your beard is good" lol, who gets this besides me? _Discovered around 1525 near the Porta del Popolo in Rome, this marble bust of the Roman deity Jupiter stands 12' 7.5" tall, believed to be originally sculpted in the 2nd century AD. Initially placed in Pope Clement's villa Madama, Jupiter of Versailles, as it is known, was transferred to Perrenot Nicolas de Granvelle in 1541 and soon thereafter displayed in a Besancon hotel in 1546. In 1683, Granvelle heir Charles-François de la Baume bestowed ownership of the bust to Louis XIV, whereupon, it was moved to Versailles' grove of the Water Theatre and the draped garment seen in the photo above was added. Finally, in 1798, Jupiter of Versailles was transferred to the Louvre where it can be seen today.Jupiter was the supreme Roman god, regarded as equivalent to Greek Zeus, and believed to be God of the sky and thunder. The Romans named the 5th planet from the sun, largest in the Solar System, Jupiter, after their chief deity.___#romanmythology#jupiter#romanart #history #ancientrome #archaeology #museum #summit_attempt#arthistory#ig #romanempire #beard #anicenthistory #mythology #travelphotography #travellife#sculpture #louvre #louvremuseum#louvreparis#louvremuseumparis#museedulouvre #museumart #eurotravel #antiquities

name: 2019-06-22 01.05.17 2071257171856976790_museedulouvre.jpg
text: « The truth is, it isn’t always easy being the person who follows their dreams. It isn’t always easy being the person who does things differently, who chooses their own journey. It isn’t easy feeling like you are falling behind, like you are existing in a completely different lane in comparison to your peers. But instead of seeing that as a disheartening thing — you have to embrace the different lane. You have to let it motivate you.And when it comes to following your dreams, you have to understand that it is so much more than quitting your day job and padding your life with freedom. Some of the greatest creatives and innovators in the world had day jobs. Henry Miller was a copywriter, and he hated it. But he did it because he knew that the security that came from a job allowed for him to pay for his apartment, and his food, and the writing utensils he used to pen his first novels. Maya Angelou was a cable car conductor. Vonnegut was a taxi driver. All of these greats did what they had to do in order to support themselves, but they never stopped elbowing their way into the world. They never stopped believing in their vision. They fought for it, no matter what life presented them with.Because that’s the thing — life will happen to you. It will weather you. But it will never defeat you. You just have to know your purpose, and believe in it with ruthless conviction. You have to be your biggest fan, even when it is difficult, even when you feel like you’re not a shining example of success. You have to keep going.So keep going. Keep going and remind yourself that there will never be a perfect time to do things differently, or to pursue something that genuinely scares you. Following your passion doesn’t work like that. It is constant work, not just physically, but mentally. You will have to do the hard things. You will break and rebuild. You will find your resilience. You will roll with every circumstance that comes up for you. You will move forward. You will push towards the person you want to be, and the life you want to live, because while following your dreams is tough — you will always be tougher. »....#france#paris #museedulouvre

name: 2019-08-14 19.29.39 2110226127571195885_museedulouvre.jpg
text: Мона Лиза и моя натянутая улыбка 😬 Натянутая, потому что этот месье в белой рубашке следил за порядком и всех жаждущих-страждущих торопил и выгонял, оно и понятно - народу дофигища! Простояли в очереди час 🥵 очередь в 4 этажа, Карл! 🤯 «Любовались» этим шедевром всего 10 секунд, точнее успели сделать 3 фото и мне очень повезло сфотографироваться на фоне, потому что пробраться через толпу поближе весьма сложно 😇 Разглядеть само полотно, которое в 5 метрах за ограждением и пуленепробиваемым стеклом просто не реально. На самом деле это безумие какое-то 🤷🏻‍♀️ Не понимаю людей, которые пришли с маленькими детьми или просто фотографируют на свой телефон (вот зачем 🙄), шумят, едят - тех, которые пришли потому что «типа надо». Меня лично интересовала эта картина и тайна, которой она окутана и увидеть я ее хотела собственными глазами. С другой стороны все хотят быть причастны к прекрасному и понять их можно 😅 Но ребята, не ходите на Мону Лизу, не тратьте своё время - смысла нет, разве что если вы хотите сделать фото для инста типа «хэй я здесь был!» #museedulouvre #monalisa

name: 2019-08-19 12.05.29 2113626448781669423_museedulouvre.jpg
text: Hoje, resolvi andar pela Rue de Rivoli, Museu do Louvre e seus arredores. Umas 4 pessoas me pediram informação e outras para que eu fizesse fotos. Nisso, um rapaz sobe no muro (tem foto pra provar) e faz pose pra mulher fotografar. E faz pose de que? De arminha do coiso. Corri pra não sobrar pra mim, mas logo me deparei com uma família que, enquanto o filho brincava de chutar uma garrafa d'água vazia, a mãe,  de cima do muro, gritava para o marido de moleton e camisa número 10 da seleção: tem que sair aquele negócio ali atrás! Aquele triângulo, Môooo! Era a pirâmide. Dei meia volta rapidinho para me livrar daquilo e quando já estava esquecendo da cena, sinto um frio subindo na espinha vendo que o homem de camisa n° 10 tira os olhos do celular e cruza os meus. Fudeu. Não deu pra fugir. Ele vem se aproximando perguntando: METRÔ? ADONDE FICÁ EL METRÔ? EL METRÔ? Eu fiz um sinal com a mão para que ele falasse mais baixo,  cheguei mais perto, olhei bem no olho dele e falei: pardon,  monsieur. Je ne comprends pas ce que vous parlez. Excusez-moi. Se a frase está certa, não tenho certeza,  mas que saí orgulhosa de mim,  ahhhh!  xxxxxxxxxxxxxxO Louvre é o museu mais visitado do mundo, foi construído em 1190 e de lá pra cá,  foram feitos vários puxadinhos. O ultimo foi a Pirâmide de vidro de Pei leoh Ming em 1988.Com cerca de 35 mil obras de artes expostas em 60 mil m2, o museu que já foi fortaleza e depois um palácio real, abriu suas portas para o público em 1792.#maristelabeltrão #Paris #andandoporparis #andandoporaí #louvre #museudolouvre #museedulouvre

text: Sutura en proceso/Work in progresspuntos de sutura quirúrgica de seda sobre tela de chaleco salvavidas/surgical silk stitches on waterproof fabric of lifejacketEn 1816, la fragata Medusa embarranca en unos bajos frente a la costa africana. Ante la escasez de botes salvavidas, se construye una balsa en la que embarcan 147 tripulantes, los cuales son abandonados cobardemente a su suerte cortando los cabos que los unían a los botes. Tras trece días dantescos, sobrevivirán solo quince marinos.El naufragio de la Medusa resultó ser un escándalo descomunal en Francia, y fue inmortalizado por Géricault en el famoso lienzo "La balsa de la Medusa". ¿Os suena de algo la historia?#labalsadelamedusa #gericault #art #sutura #proactivaopenarms #oceanviking #refugees #museedulouvre@museelouvre

name: 2019-08-26 19.05.36 2118911331156390954_museedulouvre.jpg
text: For true art lovers, the name A.C. Andre Tanama (Yogyakarta, 1982), is familiar. His works are exhibited not only in Indonesia, but also in international art galleries such as in Milan, Lisbon, Budapest and Amsterdam.At the beginning of his career, Andre often worked with religious themes, particularly related to the stories of Jesus’ crucifixion and misery. Later, he created two distinctive characters: Wayang Monyong and “Gwen Silent” — a 4-5 years-old girl, mouthless with closed eyes — who became one of the iconic works of the contemporary artist. It is said this character is a manifestation of his less happy childhood and is filled with many symbols of spirituality and religious connotations that can also be read from other works by Tanama. Gwen Silent has been largely inspired by the artist's own daughter, Gwen Sae Ilen Tanama. Not only represented on canvas, Gwen was also sculpted. These three works will go under the hammer in our Indonesian Art Sale this Wednesday. Have a closer look at them during our last viewing day at Venduehuis The Hague (Nobelstraat 5). name: 2019-08-27 16.23.21 2119554449535058219_museedulouvre.jpg
text: ¡Ceremonia de "armes fora" está muy presente en el arte medieval catalán!Se trata de un ritual caballeresco que se impuso más allá del status de caballero en el momento de explosión de la burguesía y las grandes ciudades y que se llevaba a cabo durante las ceremonias fúnebres. En ellas, distintos caballeros montados a caballo giraban sus paveses en señal de respeto al difunto. ✔ Son distintas construcciones y esculturas las que tienen presente esta ceremonia. Un ejemplo son los sepulcros del #monestirdepoblet , cuya representación se encuentra actualmente en el #museedulouvre , una delicada pieza con cristal opaco en la que podemos apreciar a la perfección dicho ritual.Pero conservamos más representaciones de esta ceremonia en casa. Un ejemplo es el fantástico sepulcro Pere IV de Queralt y su esposa Francesca de Castellnou en Santa Maria de Bell-lloc, convento fundado por la familia de los Queralt en Santa Coloma de Queralt. ✔ Podéis encontrar más información sobre esta ceremonia en la actual exposición del Museu d'Història de Barcelona@turismescq #santacolomadequeralt #armesfora #medieval #gothic #gotic #catalunya_antiga #catalunya_medieval #racons_medievals #quebonicescatalunya #monumental_catalunya #patrimonigencat #patrimonicultural #cat_imatges #catalunya_foto #ok_catalunya #ig_catalonia #somcatalunya #descobreixcatalunya #catalunyaexperience #elmeupetit_pais

name: 2019-08-27 19.31.37 2119649205371040828_museedulouvre.jpg
text: Mona Lisa ✨One of the most iconic and recognizable paintings in the world is the Mona Lisa (ca. 1503-1519) painted by Leonardo da Vinci. The unique appeal of the portrait lies in its enigmatic nature, Mona Lisa’s smile radiates mystery, sensuality and contentment. This was achieved through sfumato, Leonardo’s painting technique that softened the transition between colors. This depth and complexity of expression is the reason the Mona Lisa is regarded as the pinnacle of portraiture. The interest in the portrait was further amplified by its mysterious history: the identity of the sitter, who commissioned the painting, how long Leonardo worked on the portrait and how it entered the French royal collection are all topics of scholarly debate.

name: 2019-08-27 19.44.24 2119655637688557101_museedulouvre.jpg
text: The Vitruvian Man ✨(Italian: Le proporzioni del corpo umano secondo Vitruvio, which is translated to "The proportions of the human body according to Vitruvius"), or simply L'Uomo Vitruviano (Italian pronunciation: [ˈlwɔːmo vitruˈvjaːno]), is a drawing by Leonardo da Vinci around 1490. It is accompanied by notes based on the work of the architect Vitruvius. The drawing, which is in pen and ink on paper, depicts a man in two superimposed positions with his arms and legs apart and inscribed in a circle and square. The drawing and text are sometimes called the Canon of Proportions or, less often, Proportions of Man. It is kept in the Gabinetto dei disegni e stampe of the Gallerie dell'Accademia, in Venice, Italy, under reference 228. Like most works on paper, it is displayed to the public only occasionally, so it isn't part of the normal exhibition of the museum.

name: 2019-08-27 20.01.30 2119664243049912048_museedulouvre.jpg
text: Saint John the Baptist in the desert-Raphael -1516 Oil on canvas-Painted in 1516 for Adrien Gouffier, Cardinal Boissy, Grand Chaplain of France under Francis I, then placed in 1532 in the collegiate of Oiron by his nephew Claude Gouffier whose coat of arms were added at the top of the composition. The influence of Michelangelo's Ignudi brings this painting closer to Raphael's works in the Chigi Chapel of Santa Maria del Popolo in Rome and situates it around 1516.It was on the occasion of the entry into the royal collection that the sculptor La Lande realized the beauty of the golden oak frame that he had to preserve. This portrait was created during the high renaissance period and Raphael used his favourite technique of oil on canvas to come up with this classic piece. It is one of those paintings that made him be compared to some of his contemporaries like Titian. He is able to deliver the mood and come up with a fully detailed painting with a wonderful finish. #paris #louvre #renaissancefestival #artlover #travel #igdaily #travel #lifestyle #igtravel #travelgram #wanderlust #photography #lovetotravel #travelblog #explore #igdaily #tourism #keepexploring #beautifuldestinations #vacation #boyswhotravel #bucketlist #worldtraveler #traveladdict #hetravels #raphael #museedulouvre

text: Orsay Museum | 2019 February⠀⠀🇬🇧The Musée d’Orsay in Paris is home to some of the greatest works of French and European art produced in the 19th and early 20th centuries.⠀⠀Orsay Museum is famous for the collections of impressionist and post-impressionist art belonging to important artists such as Manet, Degas, Renoir, Cezanne, Van Gogh, Gauguin and Monet.⠀⠀The galleries of Orsay Museum are easy to walk and contemplate and the collections are very complete so if you have a few days in the city and you do not want to spending too much time inside a museum it a highly recommended option. Additionaly there is a lovely view of Paris from the old clock level of the station .⠀⠀You can buy a special ticket which allows you to enter both in the Orangerie and in the Orsay.•Orsay Müzesi | 2019⠀⠀🇹🇷Paris, Orsay Müzesi 20. yy başları ve 19. yy da Fransa ve Avrupa sanatı adına  ortaya konmuş birçok esere ev sahipliği yapmaktadır.⠀⠀Orsay, Manet, Degas, Renoir, Cezanne, Van Gogh, Gauguin ve Monet gibi birçok önemli ressama ait olan empresyonist ve post empresyonist koleksiyonları ile meşhurdur.⠀⠀Orsay galerilerini gezmesi ve izlemesi/bakması kolaydır bunun yanısıra koleksiyonlar da bir bütün halindedir. Eğer şehirde geçirebileceğiniz az gününüz varsa ve bir müzede çok uzun saatler geçirmek istemiyorsanız tavsiye edilebilecek bir müzedir. Bonus olarak müzenin duvarında olan saatin içinden şehrin çok güzel bir manzarası vardı.⠀⠀Alacağınız özel bir bilet ile hem Orsay hem de Orangerie Müzelerini gezebilirsiniz.⠀⠀ #museedorsay #museeorsay #museeorangerie #orsaymuseum #museedulouvre #louvremuseum #orsaymüzesi #louvremüzesi #orangeriemuseum #orangeriemüzesi #paris #france #fransa #manet #monet #claudemonet #cezanne #orsay #vangogh #vincentvangogh #gauguin #travelphotography #mytravel

name: 2019-08-27 23.45.26 2119776957260845576_museedulouvre.jpg
text: Своё знакомство с Парижем мы начали с самого посещаемого музея в мире, с Лувра.🏛 Если верить статистике, число посетителей Лувра достигает 10 млн. туристов в год. Это вполне оправдано, ведь длина коридоров музея составляет 42 км —марафонскую дистанцию и в ней имеется 35 тысяч экспонатов. А самыми известными шедеврами искусства в Лувре являются: картина Леонардо Да Винчи «Мона Лиза», статуя богини Афродиты «Венера Милосская», свод законов «Хаммурапи», Ника Самофракийская, статуя сидящего Рамзеса II и апартаменты Наполеона III. Перед входом в музей мы сразу же определили, какие экспонаты стоит лицезреть за отведённое время. Конечно же, первой в этом списке была самая знаменитая картина «Мона Лиза». Картина в жизни довольно  маленькая, защищена пуленепробиваемым антибликовым стеклом и сделать красивое фото с ней почти невозможно. До сих пор удивляют мои некоторые друзья, у которых есть вполне себе приличное фото с «Моной Лизой»🤔 просто КАРЛ, КАК?😂 Очевидно, увидеть все экспонаты за день — цель недостижимая. Известно, что если вы решитесь задержаться около каждого экспоната, хотя бы на 20 секунд, то вам придётся провести в Лувре почти месяц. Так что перед посещением Лувра в целях экономии времени лучше ознакомиться с примерным местоположением, интересующих вас экспонатов, удобно одеться и самое главное — не забыть взять с собой хорошее настроение.😌*При наличии студенческой ID-карты европейского университета вход бесплатный.😏 ________________________________________#travel#france #paris #pariscity #parisgram #erasmuslife #erasmus #myerasmus #travel #eurotrips #louvre #museedulouvre

name: 2019-08-28 00.37.17 2119803049238482747_museedulouvre.jpg
text: ⚠️ O QUE FAZER EM PARIS EM 3 DIAS? 🇫🇷⠀Paris é destino clichê nas viagens pela Europa, mas com certeza é uma cidade que você precisa conhecer! Quem visita Paris pela primeira vez, o roteiro de 3 dias é pequeno diante de tanta coisa para ser vista, mas já dá pra curtir muito e ficar com vontade de voltar mais vezes! 🥰⠀Dia 1️⃣: Comece pelo Arc de Triomphe, onde você pode subir o monumento e curtir a vista da Champs-Élysées! Ele fica no início da avenida mais charmosa do mundo. De lá, siga pela própria avenida passando pelas matrizes de marcas como Louis Vuitton e Cartier. 🛍 Logo depois, conheça o Petit e o Grand Palais, edifícios de belíssima arquitetura. O Petit tem entrada gratuita! De lá, siga para o Trocadero e curta a vista da Torre Eiffel, e enfim, conheça a Torre Eiffel de pertinho! Se quiser subir, nosso conselho é comprar o ingresso antes e se preparar para filas! 🗼 Por fim siga para Champs de Mars, onde você pode curtir o fim de tarde e ver a torre ser iluminada, quando ela fica ainda mais linda!⠀Dia 2️⃣: Comece o dia conhecendo o Hôtel des Invalides, que tem um jardim espetacular. 🌳  Siga de lá para a Place de La Concorde e depois o Museu do Louvre. Ele abre às 9h e quanto antes você chegar, melhor. Deixe para tirar fotos depois da visita! Do Louvre siga para o Museu d’Orsay, um dos melhores do mundo! 🖼 Saindo do museu, aprecie a vista do Rio Sena enquanto caminha até a Catedral de Notre Dame, que está em reforma após o incêndio, mas continua linda e imponente! Perto da catedral há vários restaurantes e cafés pra você conhecer! 🔓 Lembra da ponte dos cadeados de Paris? O nome dela é Pont des Arts, mas por segurança os cadeados foram retirados dela e colocados na Île de la Cité, ali pertinho, ao lado da Pont Neuf. 💙⠀Dia 3️⃣: Comece sua manhã partindo para uma visita ao Palácio de Versalhes, ele é um castelo real, um dos maiores do mundo. 🏛 Infelizmente ele não fica em Paris, e sim na cidade vizinha, por isso, reserve quase o dia todo pra ele! Dá pra chegar de ônibus ou trem. Voltando de lá, no final da tarde, vá até os Jardins de Luxemburgo, 🌲 um dos bosques mais lindos que já vimos na vida,para terminar a tarde fazendo um piquenique! 🧺

text: 🇬🇧 The Louvre Pyramide Inversée (Inverted Pyramid) is a skylight constructed in the Carrousel du Louvre, an underground shopping mall in front of the Louvre Museum in France. It may be thought of as a smaller sibling of the more famous Louvre Pyramid, yet turned upside down: its upturned base is easily seen from outside. 🇫🇷 Le Louvre Pyramide Inversée est une lucarne construite dans le Carrousel du Louvre, un centre commercial souterrain situé en face du musée du Louvre en France. On pourrait penser qu’il s’agit d’un petit frère de la plus célèbre pyramide du Louvre, pourtant renversé: sa base renversée se voit facilement de l’extérieur. 🇪🇸 La Pirámide Invertida es un tragaluz construido en el Carrousel du Louvre, un centro comercial subterráneo frente al Museo del Louvre en Francia. Puede considerarse como un hermano menor de la más famosa Pirámide del Louvre, pero al revés: su base hacia arriba se ve fácilmente desde afuera. #Spanish #French #English #Languages #Architecture #Paris #Design #Louvre #France #MuseeduLouvre #MonaLisa #Travel #Culture #Francophonie #Français #Art #Museum #Musée

name: 2019-08-28 15.00.24 2120237473293322867_museedulouvre.jpg
text: ルーヴル美術館めちゃくちゃ広い❗️約35000点もの美術品が展示されているそうです😲😲😲 どこをどう観たらいいか迷ってしまうので、今回はツアーに参加🙋‍♀️ガイドさんのお話がすごく分かりやすくて、しかも撮影時間もたくさんあって、2時間たっぷりルーヴル美術館を楽しみました😆いろんな有名作品がありますが、何と言っても楽しみにしていたのはモナリザを観ること❗️❗️一生に一度は観たい！と思っていた絵です🎵前の日までは展示室に入れなかったみたいで、急遽展示室が移動になってそうです😌観れて良かったぁ〜🤓✨他の絵よりも混み合っていましたが、朝早かったからか一番前で撮ることができました📷絵が見えた時感動して、鳥肌立っちゃいました😭さまざまな時代、様々な国の作品がたくさんあって、駆け足で作品観たので、もっとゆっくり時間をかけてみたいです😌何日かかるか分からないけど🤣💦💦笑フェルメールも観たかったなぁ〜❗️作品も素晴らしいですが、ルーヴル美術館自体も美しかったです✨#louvremuseum#museedulouvre#lagioconda #monalisa#wingedvictory #venusofmilo #statueoflibertyleadingthepeople#botticelli#arcimboldo #thefourseasons #ルーヴル美術館#モナリザ #サモトラケのニケ #ミロのヴィーナス#民衆を導く自由の女神 #ボッティチェリ #アルチンボルド #四季#france #paris#travel #trip#sightseeing #フランス #パリ#旅行 #観光 #夏休み #親子旅 #菊池家の夏休み

text: Coucou les dessineux!.Faut absolument que je vous raconte!!!.Dimanche il faisait beau (si si je vous assure! Ça arrive dans le Nord plus souvent qu’on ne le pense 😱).Du coup, soleil, dimanche, matinée à perdre ça veux dire... BRADERIE !!! 😀.Vite on va sur sabradou et on lance un œil !.Y’en a une à 5km mais que demande le peuple je vous dirais ?!! 🙈.Et la ... BIM, deux coups de foudre qui rentabilise au moins 10 braderies sans achats 😱.Là je vous présente la toile qui me plaisait la moins des deux..Un petit clin d’œil en passant devant.. mais oui!! .C’est évident!.Je la vois déjà!.Elle aura toute sa place avec un Roquefort affamé!.Vous voyez de qui je parle ? 😉.Alors qu’en pensez vous les amis? 🙂.Vous pouvez retrouver toutes mes autres toiles dans le même genre sur #liroycustom 🙂🙏🏻.#dessin #draw #drawing #art #artstagram #artwork #peint #peinture #chat #cat #marie #louvre #fanart #louvremuseum #lesaristochats #thearistocats #fan #museedulouvre #paris #comics#bd #comics #disney #disneylandparis #disneyland #disneystore #donalduck #princesse @disneylifestyle #princess #posca  @disneyfr  @disneylandparis  @disney.arts  @shopdisneyfr @poscagallery

name: 2019-08-28 18.41.10 2120348589792575925_museedulouvre.jpg
text: Sant'Anna la Vergine e il bambino con l'agnellino, opera di Leonardo da Vinci 1510/1513 esposta al Louvre di Parigi. Qui non c'era la coda per vedere il dipinto da vicino come con la Monalisa ma credetemi da parte mia l'emozione era tanta. Il blu, i colori e lo sfumato di Leonardo visti da vicino mi ipnotizzarono. Ho studiato quest'opera sui libri di testo, la conoscevo e l'ho amata molto ma solo osservarla da vicino mi ha dato una profonda conoscenza di essa.

name: 2019-08-28 19.56.27 2120386473097653050_museedulouvre.jpg
text: Музей Лувра — один из крупнейших и самый популярный художественный музей мира. Это один из старейших музеев с богатой историей коллекционирования художественных и исторических реликвий Франции, начиная со времён династии Капетингов и до наших дней.В Лувре собиралось всё, этот музей можно назвать универсальным. Его коллекции покрывают огромные географические и временные пространства: от западной Европы до Ирана через Грецию, Египет и Ближний Восток; с античности до 1848 года. Я очень тщательно готовилась к посещению Лувра: прочитала много вспомогательного материала, заранее прослушала 7 часовой аудиогид. (Готовьтесь, музей не выдает аудиогид на русском языке!!)! При этом за плечами у меня была история искусства не в одном учебном заведении, и, все равно, мои знания не могут охватить всей огромной коллекции, собранной в бывшем дворце французских королей. Действительно, этот музей потрясает не только красотой, но и масштабностью, его очень сложно обойти за один раз, и мы даже не пытались это сделать. Пожалуй, это то самое место, которое мне хочется посетить еще и, возможно, не один раз. Сказать что мне понравилось - ничего не сказать, градус моего восторга зашкаливает!!! name: 2019-08-28 20.54.22 2120415625481806915_museedulouvre.jpg
text: Le Louvre la nuit est romantique✨(France/Paris)ぶらぶら歩いて泊まっていたホテルまで帰り途中、ライトアップされた夜のルーブル美術館の前を通り、ふと昔の記憶がよみがえった。 🔖.………………………………………………………………………もう何年も前の事……。あるプチホテルの朝食ルームで朝食を食べていた時、人がいっぱいで係の人が相席で座らせていて、私が座っていた二人用の席の前にある男性が座った。.軽く挨拶をした後、「どこから来たの？」と話しかけられ、たどたどしいながらもいろいろ話をした。.その人はパリから電車で２時間ぐらいのとこに住んでいて仕事の用を兼ねて母親と数日パリに滞在しているとの事だった。.｢昼間は仕事だけど、夜どこか案内してあげるよ｣と言われ、大丈夫かなと思いつつも、この時も夏だったのでまだ明るい20時頃に出かけセーヌ川沿いを散歩した後、ライトアップされたルーブル美術館に連れてきてくれた。.「きれいでしょう✨この景色見せたくて」「うん、とてもきれいだね✨」ゴールドのライトアップが幻想的できれいだった(*´ω｀*)💕.しばらく眺めた後、カフェに入りいろいろ話をした。そしてメトロの終電がなくなる時間になってしまい、ヴェリブというレンタサイクル(あちこちにある駐輪場で借りて別のところで返却できる)で帰ることにし、１台を2人乗りしたり、時には自転車を引きながら歩いて帰った。風が気持ちよく、自転車で見る景色はまた違って楽しかったな😌.また朝食を一緒に取る約束をしてそれぞれ部屋に戻った。爽やかで紳士的な人だった☺.…………………………………………………………………………… .そんな事があったな～と思い出しながら眺めてた(*´ー｀*)よく見たらピラミッドの後ろに人がいっぱい座ってるようだったので何かやっていたのかな～👀...#フランス#フランス好き#パリ#ルーブル美術館#夕方の景色#マジックアワー#ダレカニミセタイケシキ#イルミネーション#旅スタグラム#旅好き#マイトリ#タビジョ#ヨーロッパ#ig_france#loves_france_#hello_france#ig_paris#parisjetaime#paris_focus_on#paysage#museedulouvre#genic_mag#knt_travelgram#retrip_global#retrip_paris#retrip_news#trip#voyage

text: Лувр, самый посещаемый в мире музей, ежегодно его гостями становятся около восьми с половиной миллиона человек. Являясь третьим по величине мировым музеем, Лувр демонстрирует свои сокровища на 58 500 квадратных метрах.Лувр-это гордость Франции, он очень популярен среди туристов, наравне с Собором Парижской Богоматери и Эйфелевой башней.Один из самых знаменитых музеев Европы Лувр имеет свою уникальную историю, но фактически, становление Лувра, как музея, началось во времена Великой Французской революции. Именно якобинцы создали на территории бывшего королевского дворца Центральный музей искусств, открыв свои двери для первых посетителей 10 августа 1793 года. С этого момента, Лувр часто перестраивался, расширялся, его коллекции постоянно пополнялись...📸 @subtelnyi.page ...paris #parisstyle #parisianstyle #parisparis #parisienne #parisien #style #styleblogger #stylemen #model #modelagency #modeling #modeltest #modellife #modelling #france #france🇫🇷 #francestyle #frances #vogue #voguerussia #voguefrance #vogueparis #fitnessmodel #louvre #louvremuseum #louvrepyramid #lelouvre #musee #museedulouvre

name: 2019-08-29 07.35.05 2120738104301760112_museedulouvre.jpg
text: Dag 3: Ännu en svettig dag i Paris! Vid Tour Saint-Jaques fanns det lite, lite skugga och det visste alla parisare för skuggplatserna var mer eller mindre alla upptagna! ➡️ Men jag har spenderat flertalet timmar inomhus med AC! Alla väder är bra museiväder. Väldigt glad efter besök på Musée du Cluny, Frankrikes nationella medeltidsmuseum. ➡️ Tittade sedan på ännu fler artefakter och konstverk på Musée du Louvre. Använde kartan över Louvren som solfjäder för det var fanimej det enda den dög till! Har aldrig gått så vilse i hela mitt liv. (➡️ Men var glad ändå!) Var nog den enda där som inte köade för att se Mona-Lisa, men såg faktiskt mästerverket förra gången och nu kände jag att andra mästerverk kallade på min uppmärksamhet. Louvren hade kvällsöppet, timmarna gick, och jag gick ut när solen höll på att gå ner och bara tjoff, där försvann den dagen?! Jag är helt slut mentalt, så många intryck, men ojoj vilka  fantastiska intryck! Bonne nuit! #solotravel #historylife #museumlife #paris #museeducluny #museedulouvre #selfiepinne

name: 2019-08-29 10.31.49 2120827064331720229_museedulouvre.jpg
text: In 1939 as Hitler came knocking on the door of France the keepers of the great art of Paris sprang into action. While Hitler and his art loving friends headed to Paris with a shopping list of must have pieces of art, the Mona Lisa and the treasures of the Musée du Louvre were at the top.  Jacques Jaujard the director of France’s National Museum and René Huyghe, curator of paintings devised a plan to save the art of the Louvre. On August 25, the Louvre was closed for cleaning for three days. However, what really happened on those three days would alter the plans of the dictator and his greedy plans. On those three days, the staff of the Louvre and students worked around the clock removing paintings from their frames, rolled and placed in crates. On the 28th, more than a twelve hundred crates left the Louvre headed to the Loire Valley. There was one special crate that would travel on its own. The most famous painting of the Louvre, the Mona Lisa would be packed separately and without any of the markings that each crate left the Louvre with. Only the initials MN were noted on the outside as she was strapped to a stretcher of an ambulance and drove out of the Louvre. Spending three months at Chambord in November, she would move to the Château de Louvigny and keep moving every few months. Always trying to outrun the German forces as they came closer and closer.  Following the German surrender on May 8, 1945 the artwork began their return to the Louvre. On June 16, 1945, the Mona Lisa was hanging back on the walls of the Musée du Louvre and on October 6, 1947 the museum was reopened to the public. Without the quick thinking and work of Jacques Jauhard and René Huyghe and the countless people that gave their time, most of the Louvre would have been lost. #paris #parishistoryavecclaudine #monalisa #museedulouvre #art #wwii

name: 2019-08-29 20.58.59 2121142732199082092_museedulouvre.jpg
text: Tal día como hoy de 1780 nacía en Montaunan Jean-Auguste Dominique Ingres, pintor neoclásico francés, aunque en su obra también podemos encontrar tanto el romanticismo como el realismo.Extraordinario dibujante, cuyo predominio en la composición defendió siempre, especialmente contra los pintores románticos, partidarios del color, su obra provocó la admiración de artistas como Degas y Picasso. Fue alumno del neoclásico David, y se mudó a Roma a los 21 años, becado por la República Napoleónica.Gran admirador del gran Rafael Sanzio, Ingres desarrolló un estilo personal y en ocasiones, subversivo, con composiciones fuertemente criticadas. A pesar de todo ello, sus pinturas de temas, figuras históricas y sus retratos, muy apreciados por la burguesía del Imperio, lo encumbraron hasta su fallecimiento en la capital francesa.🖼: Edipo y la esfinge (1808).👨‍🎨: Jean-Auguste Dominique Ingres (1780-1867).📍: Musée du Louvre, París.#arte #art #artista #artist #taldiacomohoy #onthisday #historia #history #arthistory #historiadelarte #museo #museos #musee #museum #museums #galeria #gallery #galleries #pintura #cuadro #cuadros #cultura #culture #pintor #pintores #historyofart #instamuseum #ingres #museedulouvre #louvre

name: 2019-08-29 22.09.10 2121178057021465264_museedulouvre.jpg
text: _큐피드의 키스로 환생한 프시케.큐피드의 이름은 라틴어 욕망에서 비롯되었고, 그리스어로는 에로스다.프시케의 이름은 그리스어로숨, 영혼의 의미라고 한다.루브르박물관에서 본 카노바의 작품은 그 자체만으로도 의미 있지만.진정한 사랑을 표현한다는큐피드의 푸시케의 이름이.욕망, 에로스 그리고 숨, 영혼이라는개념이라는 것이 꽤 흥미로웠다.때론 이질적으로도 보이는 두 가지 성질이 함께일 때에야그 진정한 빛을 보일 때가 있다...마치 불로 구운 뜨거운 갈비를이름마저 차가운 냉면과 함께 먹을 때화룡정점을 찍는 것처럼.나는 왜 꼭 먹는걸로끝을 안 맺으면 안 되는 걸까.하긴 사랑보다는고기와 음식에 대해서 해박하지_

name: 2019-08-30 03.31.48 2121340428579009078_museedulouvre.jpg
text: MUSÉE DU LOUVREAprès avoir passé au moins deux heures à assimiler les grands chefs-d'œuvre du plus grand musée du monde, quittez-le et passez devant la pyramide en métal et verre créée par l'architecte américano-chinois IM Pei. Cette construction ultramoderne a été achevée en 1989 et a suscité la controverse en raison de son contraste saisissant avec l'aspect classique du musée. Commandée par le regretté président François Mitterrand, cette ville est désormais un monument historique. #louvre #museedulouvre #paris #parisparis

text: Ya quedamos con que no es posible recorrer todo el Louvre en un solo día, por lo que yo ya había hecho mi investigación y una de las colecciones que más me daban ganas de ver era la de antigüedades egipcias....Quizá por qué ya me sabía un poco de su historia, por que en mi infancia; mi madre y mi hermano estaban obsesionados con la cultura egipcia 🤷🏻‍♀️..Ya se imaginarán la emoción de ver en vivo la esfinge de Tanis. Una esfinge que fue tallada en el año 2600 a.C es simplemente increíble !..📸Colección egipcia, Musée du Louvre, Paris, Francia ..#greatsphinxoftanis #tanis #egipto #egiptologia #osiris #neftis #horus #museedulouvre #louvre #museodelouvre #paris #art

name: 2019-08-30 05.56.19 2121413178530020299_museedulouvre.jpg
text: Back in #NYC momentarily, but still thinking about the whimsical surprises hiding on the surface of the amazing embossed armor of King Henri II of France, now in the Louvre. Though the main program of the armor's sculpted decoration tells the rather serious story of the Roman general Pompey, the margins and small pieces of the elements are decorated with unexpected, often comical details, like the margins of an illuminated manuscript. The scaled faces of fantastical sea-creatures peek out from the toe caps of the sabatons (1st image) and naturalistic snails crawl along the back edges of the pauldrons, or shoulder defenses (2nd image). #armsandarmor #armor #henriii #museedulouvre #inthedetails #steel #repoussé #metalwork #inthemargins #arthistoryadventures #throwbackthursday #creaturefeature

name: 2019-08-30 15.04.22 2121689020884050553_museedulouvre.jpg
text: Самая большая проблема, с которой сталкиваются посетители мировых музеев масштаба Лувра – это очереди в кассы и столпотворения людей везде (!). Число любителей искусства, способных позволить себе путешествовать и смотреть мир, год от года растет, а стены галерей при этом не расширяются. Толкаться среди картин, как в столичном метро в час пик, мало кому хочется, и хотя в Лувре этого почти не избежать, минимизировать проблему можно.Настоящий бич этого музея – огромное число групп организованных туристов, прежде всего из стран Азии. Именно они создают «пробки» в галерее, плотно, в несколько рядов, окутывая самые знаковые экспонаты. Стоит быть готовым к тому, что насладиться взглядом Джоконды Леонардо да Винчи в тишине и одиночестве вам не удастся никогда. (Я не рассматриваю вариант, когда вы войдете в музей одним из первых в момент открытия, держа наготове билет с планом Лувра и, как спринтер, броситесь бежать по указателям к Моне Лизе. Тогда да, вам будут гарантированы несколько минут с ней почти наедине).Очевидно, что чем более ранний сеанс посещения Лувра вы забронируете, тем приятнее будет ваш визит. Если есть возможность, выбирайте первый в 9.00, и подходите к музею в точно назначенное время или чуть заранее. Кстати, даже если вы купите билет через интернет, но придете на 30 минут позже вашего сеанса, то придется стоять на общих основаниях в очереди вместе с другими посетителями. У меня не возникло желания проверять, насколько строго соблюдается это правило сотрудниками музея, но оно есть и указано на вашем электронном билете.Другой вариант избежать адских столпотворений – дождаться вечера, когда основная масса групп покидает музей. В этом случае стоит выбрать для визита день, когда Лувр открыт до 21.45 (это среда и пятница)...📸 @subtelnyi.page ...paris #parisstyle #parisianstyle #parisparis #parisienne #parisien #style #styleblogger #stylemen #model #modelagency #modeling #modeltest #modellife #modelling #france #france🇫🇷 #francestyle #frances #vogue #voguerussia #voguefrance #vogueparis #fitnessmodel #louvre #louvremuseum #louvrepyramid #lelouvre #musee #museedulouvre

name: 2019-08-30 20.16.51 2121846297718978835_museedulouvre.jpg
text: Part 1 of 3 check out my profile for the full picture Napoleon once renamed the Louvre to Musée Napoleon and expanded its collection by 5,000 pieces. The pieces were, however, returned to the original owners when the military leader was defeated.During his rule, Napoleon hung the Mona Lisa in his private bedroom. This was the first time the Mona Lisa was ever hung. The second time she was hung was when Jacqueline Kennedy arranged for the painting to tour museums in Washington DC and New York.•••••#museedulouvre #louvremuseum #france #paris #wanderlust #beautifuldestinations #travelcouple #travelgram #travelphotography #travel #worldtraveler

name: 2019-08-30 20.22.31 2121849143948593136_museedulouvre.jpg
text: Part 2 of 3 check out my profile for the full picture The Musée du Louvre was not originally museum. It was a fortress that was built in 1190. In the 16th century, it was turned from a fortress into a royal palace. It was only in 1793, after the French Monarchy moved to the Palace of Versailles, that the first Louvre museum was opened to the public, and offered just 537 paintings.•••••#museedulouvre #louvremuseum #france #paris #wanderlust #beautifuldestinations #travelcouple #travelgram #travelphotography #travel #worldtraveler

name: 2019-08-30 20.31.40 2121853758236680941_museedulouvre.jpg
text: Part 3 of 3 check out my profile for the full picture Musee du Louvre is The Biggest Museum in the World. It is so big that it is humanely impossible to see all the museum has to offer in one visit. How long would it take you? Well, if you ever have 100 days spare, you could probably squeeze in every piece of art, but you could only spend 30 seconds on each piece – and that’s if you were there all day, every day. The museum offers 380,000 pieces in total – but not all of collection is exhibited to the public.•••••#museedulouvre #louvremuseum #france #paris #wanderlust #beautifuldestinations #travelcouple #travelgram #travelphotography #travel #worldtraveler

text: | Vendredi lecture | Paul Véronèse a peint plusieurs repas évangéliques : celui de chez Simon, celui de chez Lévi, la Cène évidemment. Thème essentiel dans l'Évangile, on le retrouve dans bien d'autres religions. La transformation, lors des noces de Cana, de l'eau en vin est directement liée à la peinture, qui nous permet de transformer le réel, de le transposer ailleurs, de nous faire admirer ce que nous n'aurions pas été capables d'admirer sans elle..🎨 Paul Véronèse, Les Noces de Cana (détail), 1562-1963, musée du Louvre, Paris..#vendredilecture #michelbutor #histoiredelart #veronese #louvre #louvremuseum #museedulouvre #peinture #lacene

name: 2019-08-30 22.15.05 2121905808852897464_museedulouvre.jpg
text: Le Radeau de La Méduse, oeuvre réalisée entre 1818 et 1819 par le peintre français Théodore Géricault 🎨⁠Ce tableau, de très grande dimension (491 cm de hauteur et 716 cm de largeur), représente le naufrage de la frégate Méduse qui avait pour objectif de rétablir la domination coloniale française en Afrique de l'Ouest. ⁠⁠Provoquant la controverse à son époque, cette oeuvre est désormais exposée au musée du Louvre, où vous pouvez gratuitement utiliser votre application Tellnoo📱durant votre visite.⁠⁠***⁠Pour en apprendre plus sur ce tableau mais aussi découvrir d’autres oeuvres du même peintre : http://bit.ly/RadeaudelaMéduse⁠***⁠⁠#musée #art #peinture #visite #patrimoine #patrimoinefrançais #audioguide #tourisme #culture #découverte #Paris #France⁠ #radeaudelameduse #louvres #museedulouvre #musee #decouvrirensemble #patrimoineculturel #tableau #oeuvre #theodoregericault #tellnoo #art #peintre #gericault #artiste

text: Ce lieu est magnifique d’architecture et d’histoire. Petite anecdote, lors de la mise en place de l’obélisque sur la #placedelaconcorde l’ingénieur en charge n’était pas sur de son coup, il s’est alors mis dans l’axe de l’obélisque lors de la bascule. Si celle-ci basculait de l’autre côté il aurait été mort écrasé car il préférait cela plutôt que de mourir de honte ou lynché par la foule. Voilà 😉 #museedulouvre #jardindestuileries #paris #obelisque

text: Pyramide du LouvreVoilà la photo que je voulais absolument vous faire voir, et qui m'a motivé à faire des poses longues d'autres lieux incontournables de Paris. Ce qui est incroyable c'est que la photo d'origine, sans retouche était déjà très proche de cette version. Je suis de plus en plus attentif aux détails, c'est pourquoi j'ai dû modifier certaines parties. Je vous ferai voir en story l'Avant/Après  retouche.This is the picture that I absolutely wanted to show you, and that motivated me to make long exposures from other famous places in Paris. What is amazing is that the original photo without editing was already very close to this version. I am more and more attentive to the details, which is why I had to modify some parts. I will show you in the story Before / After editing.#louvremuseum #museedulouvre #lecmn #parisisbeautiful #parismaville #paris #longexposure #pariscartepostale #oh_my_france #amazingfrance #Reflection_gram #igparis #igparisiloveyou #parisfeatured #best_france_photos #best_france #france #louvrepyramid #louvre #lelouvre #pyramidedulouvre

name: 2019-08-31 01.18.07 2121997920441485286_museedulouvre.jpg
text: .🇫🇷 Le vendredi c’est #LaModeAuLouvre !-Cette peinture, réalisée en 1751 par Chardin, met en scène dans un intérieur bourgeois une femme assise sur une bergère garnie d’un tissu à rayures vertes et blanches. La tête du modèle est couverte d’un bonnet blanc noué sous le menton.-La dame est vêtue d’un mantelet de lingerie blanche. Celle-ci recouvre une robe à la française et sa large jupe de soierie blanche semée de fleurs rose. L’ensemble des tissus voluptueux laisse entrevoir le corsage de la jeune femme. A cette période, celui-ci est ajusté sur le devant et sur les côtés.-Elle active un instrument de musique, appelé serinette, qui est posé sur ses genoux. Cet objet est témoin d’un milieu raffiné et est plus un objet d’amusement qu’un véritable instrument de musique.-📍 Aile Sully, salle 921.- - - -🌍 It’s #FashionFriday at the Louvre!-This painting, made in 1751 by Chardin, depicts in a bourgeois interior a woman sitting on a wing chair decorated with a fabric with green and white stripes. Her head is covered with a white cap tied under her chin.-The lady is dressed in a mantelet of voluptuous white lingerie. This one covers a French dress and its large white silk skirt with pink flowers. All the vaporous fabrics reveal the young woman's bodice. During this period, it is adjusted on the front and sides.-She plays a musical instrument, called a serinette, which is placed on her lap. This instrument is the sign of a sophisticated environment and is more an object of amusement than a real musical instrument.-📍  Sully wing, room 921.-📷 © Musée du Louvre / René-Gabriel Ojéda... #MuseeDuLouvre #Louvre

text: Have you been to Louvre? Louvre is the most spectacular museum I’ve been to..The first time I’ve visited was 10 years ago and I remember being exhausted after hours of walking with an audio guide and learning about paintings. This time was similar 😂.The most famous piece of art held in Louvre is Mona Lisa and to see her we had to join a separate queue..It took about 50 min and you get about 30 sec to admire her famous smile..Tip- book your ticket online so you avoid queuing and prepare yourself for 3-4 hours min..Photo by mum 📸 Not bad mum not bad.. 🥰

name: 2019-08-31 05.23.22 2122121356979708312_museedulouvre.jpg
text: ¡Por fin viernes!#curiosidades ¿Qué soléis hacer los fines de semana? ¿Qué otros hobbies tenéis además de leer?El arte tiene mil y una formas: la pintura, la escultura, la arquitectura, la escritura, la música, las artes visuales, la fotografía, el teatro, la danza, la cocina... tenemos un sinfín de posibilidades a escoger.En mi caso, siempre me llamó muchísimo la atención las Bellas Artes y más en concreto, la pintura. Hace algunos años, estudié Historia del Arte y siempre me maravilló la figura de Leonardo da Vinci y todo lo que envuelve a este personaje. Cada vez que podía, compraba libros que hablara de este artista que tan influyente fue en la época del Renacimiento.La "Mona Lisa" te atrapa cuando la ves (sobre todo por primera vez), pero este genio también tiene otros cuadros preciosos como por ejemplo "La dama del Armiño", además de unos dibujos espectaculares. ¿Cuál es vuestro artista favorito?PD: puede ser de cualquier ámbito 😊#friday #happyfriday #hobbies #painting #davinci #monalisa #gioconda #ladywithanermine #historiadelarte #finearts #museedulouvre #artgallery #renacimiento #cultura #instagram #instalibros #bookstagramespaña #instagrammers #booksfordays #booksbooksbooks📚 #booksandflowers #booksphotography #recomendaciones #amorporloslibros♥ #booknerd #bookish #bookswarm

text: There are over 38,000 pieces of art in the Musée  du Louvre, and sadly many go to see only one painting. I tried to compile a list of 10 paintings to see instead of the Mona Lisa, which is almost impossible for me. These are some of my favorites you should see, each with there own amazing story behind them. From the painting of the sister of one of one of the greatest French artists, to the only portrait Napoleon ever sat for that was also never finished and the altarpiece of the patron saint of Paris. In my newest article for Bonjour Paris discover each of these beautiful pieces. Link in bio #paris #parishistoryavecclaudine #museedulouvre #louvre #art #napoleon #delacroix

name: 2019-08-31 18.09.02 2122506743925190749_museedulouvre.jpg
text: Les parents d'un jeune garçon veulent connaître son futur métier. Ils disposent quatre objets sur le sol:une bouteille de vodka, un livre saint , un billet de 200 euros et un magazine porno.Le mari explique à sa femme:- Si notre bébé prend la vodka, il sera alcoolique ou barman. S'il prend le livre saint , il rentrera dans les ordres. S'il choisit l'argent, il sera homme d'affaire. Et s'il prend le magazine, ce sera un voyou.L'enfant entre à quatre pattes dans la pièce, voit les objets, et les prend tous les quatre.La mère, horrifiée, s'exclame:- Oh mon Dieu! Il veut faire de la politique! . text: ✈️유럽여행 +10DAYS FRANCE PARIS🇫🇷 -루브르박물관 - 생트샤펠성당 - 노트르담 - 사랑해벽 - 사크레쾨르 성당 - 마르스광장(화이트에펠)..-루브르박물관. 투어를 신청해 돌아보았다. 모나리자와 밀로의 비너스, 민중을 이끄는 자유의여신[들라크루아]를 보았다. 미술책에서나 보던걸 실제로 보니 신기했다. 개인적으로는 민중을 이끄는 자유의 여신이 더 인상 깊었다.-생트샤펠 성당은 2층으로 올라가자마자 스테인글라스가 시선을 사로잡았다. 어느 성당보다 스테인글라스가 화려하고 아름다워 멍하니 쳐다만 보게 되었다. 다른 성당에 가도 이런 느낌은 받지 못할 것 같다.-지나가다 노트르담 대성당을 보았다. 불에 타 공사중이었다. 볼때마다 아쉽기도 하고 슬프기도 하였다. 공사가 끝나고 예전 모습을 찾을때가 되면 꼭 방문해 보고 싶다. -사랑해벽은 몽마르뜨에 위치해있고 사크레쾨르 성당을 가는길에 들렸다. 한글은 3군데나 있다. 앞에서 사진도 찍었다. 하지만 다른사람들이 쳐다봐 호다닥 찍고 나왔다.-사크레쾨르 성당은 생각보다 별로였다. 그 앞의 계단에 앉아 맥주를 마시며 파리시내 전경을 바라보는게 더 좋았다.- 해가 지고 마르스 광장으로가서 다른 한국인동행을 만나 같이 화이트 에펠을 기다리며 맥주와 샴페인을 마셨다. 매우 좋았다. 화이트에펠은 생각만큼 인상깊진 않았다. 하지만 파리의 마지막 밤이라 열심히 눈에 저장하였다..#유럽여행 #유럽 #프랑스 #파리 #프랑스여행 #유럽한달여행 #루브르박물관 #모나리자 #레오나르도다빈치 #밀로의비너스 #민중을이끄는자유의여신 #들라크루아 #생트샤펠 #노트르담대성당 #사랑해벽 #몽마르뜨 #사크레쾨르성당 #europe #france #paris #museedulouvre #louvremuseum #louvrepyramid #monalisa #leonardodavinci #venus #saintchapelle #montmarte #lesmurdesjetaime #sacrecoeur

name: 2019-09-01 00.15.32 2122691207613313191_museedulouvre.jpg
text: .🏺La galerie Campana, aile Sully, présente l’évolution de la céramique grecque sur cinq siècles. _🕰Tout commence avec le style géométrique (IXe-VIIIe s. av. J.-C.), dont le décor austère et structuré s’ouvre progressivement à la figure humaine et aux scènes narratives. Le VIIe s. av. J.-C. est orientalisant avec, parallèlement à la production athénienne, des ateliers très talentueux comme ceux de Corinthe et de la Grèce de l’Est qui privilégient les frises décoratives, qu’elles soient animales, végétales ou fantastiques. Au VIe s. av. J.-C., Athènes reprend la première place avec l’explosion de son répertoire mythologique et la maîtrise de la technique des figures noires qui laissera sa place, à la fin du siècle, à celle des figures rouges. Le Ve s. av. J.-C. est encore celui de la céramique attique, âge d’or durant lequel les peintres de talent sont nombreux et la perfection du dessin à son comble. Enfin, le IVe s. av. J.-C. voit les limites de cette production de qualité avec encore de très belles réalisations dans la partie occidentale du monde grec, en Italie méridionale._____________📍Aile Sully 1er étage Galerie Campana_____________📷©️InsideTheLouvre / @n.bousser _____________#art #culture #patrimoine #louvre #museedulouvre #louvremuseum #céramique #grece #greek  #museum #athènes #paris #france🇫🇷 #france #insta #instagram #instatravel #instatrip #instapic #galeriecampana #travel #trip

name: 2019-09-01 03.29.53 2122789019017484355_museedulouvre.jpg
text: Guess the September thematic ! 👇Liberale da Verona, l'Enlèvement d'Europe, huile sur panneau, H.0.39 x L. 1.18 m, musée du LouvrePhoto @nadelshaThis painted panel used to decore the front side of a wedding chest - named cassone during the #Renaissance. The artist Liberale da Verona (ca. 1445-1526) who realized this #painting around 1470, depicted in three different scenes, the abduction of Europe by Zeus⚡who took a bull appearence. 🐂After kidnapping the young beauty in front of her sisters, the god and his new love fled away above the #sea.🌊Once again, Zeus⚡will have used his powers to obtain love satisfaction !❤ 🤓One specific element in this panel will be our next thematic... what do you think ?Share your opinion with us ! 👇_____Devinez notre thème de septembre!👇 Ce panneau peint decorait l'intérieur d'un coffre de mariage - appelé #cassone à la Renaissance. L'artiste Liberale da Verona (b.1445-1526) qui réalisa cette #peinture vers 1470, représente en trois scènes différentes, l'enlèvement de la jeune mortelle Europe par le dieu Zeus qui revêt pour l'occasion l'apparence d'un taureau! 🐂Une fois encore Zeus use de ses pouvoirs pour obtenir satisfaction amoureuse!❤Après avoir enlevé la jeune femme sous les yeux de ses soeurs, Zeus l'entraîne au-dessus de la #mer.🌊 🤓Un élément spécial de ce panneau sera notre thème de septembre... qu'en pensez-vous?Partagez votre avis avec nous!👇  ___ #LiberaledaVerona #italianartist #Renaissance #artlovers #arthistory #histoiredelart #ohtableau 🖼 #artoftheday #museedulouvre

text: کلیسای جامع نوتْرْدام پاریس (به فرانسوی: Cathédrale Notre Dame de Paris) کلیسای معروفی در شهرپاریس است. نوتردام از قرن یازدهم بر پاریس مشرف بوده‌است و از مظاهر ملی و فرهنگی فرانسه محسوب می‌شود. این کلیسا در جزیره سیته در میانه رود سن و درمنطقه چهارم در مرکز پاریس واقع شده‌است. هر سال ۱۳ میلیون نفر از آن بازدید می‌کنند.Photo by: @travel_with_sara_ghz________________________________________#parisfrance#parislovers#arcdetriomphe#france#travelphotography #adventure#tourist#city #placestovisit#travelblogger#citylife#cityview#discovertheworld#travels#bestcity#wonderfulplaces#traveladdicted#travelling#museedulouvre#louvreparis#louvremuseum#ig_europe#europe#europe_vacations#europe_pics#europe_greatshots#landscapephotography#globefever

name: 2019-09-01 03.35.08 2122791667636159012_museedulouvre.jpg
text: Los 3 imprescindibles del Museo más famoso del mundo..La Gioconda, La Venus y Niké (mi favorita) .En realidad es que el museo completo es imprescindible... me encantaría poder venir más días (así en plural, por qué es enorme y hay mil cosas que ver)..En recorrer lo que yo quería ver, un top 10 de cosas que eran un MUST (al menos para mi) tardé de las 9 a las 6pm y estaba agotada ..Obvio en las más famosas como lo es La Mona Lisa, la gente se aglomera 😬 y tienes que hacer fila ...En fin, igual vale la pena 🤷🏻‍♀️..Eso si, jamás pero JAMÁS sueltes tu mapa 🤦🏽‍♀️ o te perderás como yo; que tarde en encontrar una salida aproximadamente por unos 40 min 😅..📸 Museé de Louvre, Paris, Francia..#museedulouvre #louvre #museodelouvre #paris #gioconda #venus #samotracia #psique #napoleon #davinci #vermeer #monet #canova #sanzio #delacroix #miguelangel #Rembrandt #giotto #art

text: " A la suite d'un évènement dramatique, Elsa se retrouve plongée dans un profond désespoir. name: 2019-09-01 16.41.32 2123187478786497510_museedulouvre.jpg
text: Вот у других ниша лучше!⠀Сидели с девочками @aniaholz и @fedina_nadezhda обсуждали ниши друг друга и я понимаю, что в каждой сфере столько нюансов. Раньше я часто себя ловила на мысли, что у меня ниша какая-то мягко говоря не очень, а вот у других то да, там и средний чек выше, и маржа хорошая такая, и вложений особых не требуется — красота!⠀Сидим разбираем каждого, и тут видишь всю изнанку, уже не так все красочно, тут и минусы подъехали, но эти минусы не могут быть объективными. Вот, к примеру, @egorkuroedov занимается лестницами, тут сотрудничество с блоггерами такая себе история, нужна реклама посерьёзнее, лестницы это не покупка на эмоциях.⠀Есть ниши, которые работают от сезона к сезону — туризм, свадьбы, тут тоже нужно очень хорошо постараться. У всех своя специфика, самое главное, я считаю, чтобы у тебя душа лежала к тому делу, которым уже занимаешься или только планируешь. А ещё важно учиться, так ты избавишься от кучи ошибок и сэкономишь своё время.⠀Я зимой думала, что СММ и салоны красоты это прям вау ниша, легкие деньги )))) А оказалось там стооолько нюансов, особенно на этапе формирования команды.⠀И вот сейчас мне кажется, что фотографам лучше всех))) Вложил в обучение, в оборудование и отбивай свои бабки, отбил — молодец, теперь можно хорошо жить и откладывать.⠀Потому что в моей сфере — не такой большой средний чек, мне постоянно нужно вкладывать в съёмки, из каждого заказа — в себестоимость, и чтобы заработать нужно много заказов, это опять же реклама⠀Что касается фотографов я понимаю, что там все глубже и это просто мой взгляд со стороны⠀#paris #france #museedulouvre #louvre #minsk #belarus

name: 2019-09-01 19.38.17 2123276438235858433_museedulouvre.jpg
text: Touring Musee du LouvreWe planned ahead and reserved for a 9:00 am arrival.  So, we planned ahead, but woke up at 8:38am.  I saw the time and jumped up and said, “We gotta go!”.The time slot reservation enabled us go to the non-existent line where all the other people who do not get advanced tickets.  This was in addition to our purchased Paris Museum Pass (highly recommend you do this). .Like everyone else we headed straight to the Mona Lisa.  As soon as we entered the museum, we saw a sign that read there was 30 minute wait to the Mona Lisa.  Doug said, “This isn’t Disneyland.” Meaning, that Disneyland knows their time science…However, we did get up to the temporary location of the famous painting in less time.  Once inside the room, we were hurried along like little kids, a few at a time. And, once in front of the painting, you had about 5 seconds to view it.  So, we took a photo of it to get some memory of it.  So, one of the photos I took of it is a poster which allowed me to see a better image of it. LOL. Well, at least I got to “see it” for real… .The museum is spectacular as far as this former palace is concerned. We enjoyed seeing Leonardo da Vinci’s other works, the Venus de Milo, the Winged Victory of Samothrace, and other great works..Yes, we did the touristy pose at the Pyramids…what can I say?!.#honeymooninparis #myadventureswithdoug #traveleurope #paris #france #museedulouvre #louvre #monalisa #museesdeparis

name: 2019-09-01 21.08.25 2123321801413487050_museedulouvre.jpg
text: Usar a expressão “à frente do seu tempo”, talvez seja um tanto quanto batido para brevemente falarmos sobre Leonardo da Vince.Curiosidade. O grande motor propulsor de Leonardo era a curiosidade, acredito que por isso ele recitava de forma introspectiva trechos de A divina Comédia de Dante. No Capitulo 33 Walter Isaacson cita uma frese de Einstein, “Não tenho nenhum talento especial. Sou apenas apaixonadamente curioso.Muitas vezes Leonardo foi visto por seus patronos (Sforza, Médici, Bórgia, entre outros como Papas, clérigos e até o Rei da França Francisco I) como procrastinador, mas, muitas das vezes que uma obra era interrompida era por que nas palavras do autor “Ele (Leonardo) gostava muito mais do desafio da concepção do que das tarefas repetitivas que levavam a conclusão”. Biografia escrita de maneira sucinta, porem rica em detalhes, e de forma não linear, ou seja, o autor vai nos guiando pelas obras, esboços, cadernos e anotações de da Vince e assim nos apresenta o momento da vida, lugares e intenções de Leonardo. Sem contar que durante a leitura nos deparamos com outras personalidades bem conhecidas como Maquiavel, Michelangelo, César Bórgia entre outros.Por fim vale ressaltar que Isaacson não é o biografo que “passa panos” para o biografado, ele nos mostras as facetas de Leonardo, as suas associações a tiranos, suas paixões, fraquezas e vontades.#leonardodavinci #monalisa #museedulouvre #michelangelo #maquiavel #biografia #intrinseca

name: 2019-09-01 22.15.08 2123355378511826013_museedulouvre.jpg
text: Some headless saints, courtesy of the Louvre... ————————————————————————Valérie de Limoges (13th cent.), escorted by angels, presenting her head as credentials to her confessor St. Martial, so that she may be dispatched to martyrdom and Paradise, from whence she might haunt the Pagan who ungracefully severed her head. One of the founding members, along with Paris’ Saint Denis, of France’s Club Céphalophore.Jean-Baptiste (1513-1516), Da Vinci’s final work and filled with a lifetime of artistic learning. Jean-Baptiste is in full (with head) androgynous form, the cross of piety in one hand and a fabulous leopard skin wrap in the other. Taken moments before Salomé decided that instead of her usual fare, she would greatly prefer Jean-Baptiste’s head on a silver platter as a thank you for her burlesque dancing.My two favorite works at the Louvre. I took no photos of La Joconde/The Mona Lisa despite seeing her. The painting itself, behind a combo of space, security, and glass, is not about the artwork itself. You cannot experience the artwork at all. There are no smells, feelings, or eye-watering details elicited. La Joconde should be take more as a post-post-modern art installation, in which you are hustled like cattle with a gaggle of incomprehensible tourists, all of whom violate the “no photos” sign, as they struggle to get selfies with the most famous image in the world. There are smells, feelings, and details—none of which you find pleasing. This experience—as recent installation art tends to be—is the real exhibition we came to see.#livesofthesaints #cephalophore #hagiography #theonomy #biblestories #martyrdom #headlesshorsemen #icons #catholicism #museedulouvre #leonardodavinci #paris #touristculture #travelswithmyhat #lajoconde #lagioconda #monalisa #sculpture #painting #modernart #postpostmodern #medievalhistory #europeanhistory #renaissance

text: “Uma pergunta: você já ficou nesta posição antes? Já tirou fotos de braços abertos, se atreveu a sair abrindo os braços por aí, para qualquer brisazinha que bate?MEUS PARABÉNS. Se esta é sua postura diante da vida, grandes chances de você ser mais saudável. Minha experiência de anos pesquisando e trabalhando com dores me mostra que, se uma mente pode adoecer o corpo, e se o corpo doente deixa a mente abalada, a via é de mão dupla: a mente positiva mantém o corpo saudável. E, a-haa: o corpo em atitude positiva eleva o estado mental! E os estudos têm comprovado isto. Tente adotar a postura que descrevi da minha amiga e contar uma história triste ao mesmo tempo. Difícil.” - Por: Juliana Torres, retirado do cabecaleve.com⠀#musee #museedulouvre #louvre #louvremuseum #louvrepyramid #lelouvre #paris #parisparis #parisfrance #eurotrip #euro #europa #trip #openarms #openmind #arms

It is located in the Louvre Palace, originally built as a fortress and later became the main residence of the French kings. name: 2019-09-02 17.29.04 2123936169449310315_museedulouvre.jpg
text: Yo no entiendo mucho de arte, pero puedo entender como este cuadro llegó a convertirse en una imagen tan famosa que un solo ojo ya te dice que se trata de La Gioconda. Y es que podría decirse que el éxito de esta pintura se debe a un fenómeno de masas que nació en 1911, gracias al famoso robo.La Gioconda fue robada el 21 de agosto, lunes, día en el que el Louvre permanecía cerrado. El italiano Vincenzo Peruggia había sido trabajador del museo, por lo que además de conocer el mecanismo de las puertas, también contaba con la indumentaria que le haría pasar desapercibido. Hay que decir que no era un cuadro muy reconocido más allá de los entendidos de arte y que figuraba en un pasillo del Museo del Louvre como cualquier otro, de ahí la facilidad de Peruggia para, sin rodeos, descolgarlo e introducirlo por debajo de su camisa. Como veis, el robo en sí no fue nada de otro mundo. De otro mundo fue el alboroto que se armó al darse cuenta el personal, un día después, de que La Mona Lisa había sido robada. La noticia se extendió rápidamente, y el hueco que dejó el cuadro en la pared fue visitado por cientos de personas, ansiosas de comprobar si lo que decían los medios era cierto. Hubo varios acusados, entre ellos Pablo Picasso y Guillaume Apollinaire.Finalmente, dos años después, Vicenzo Peruggia fue localizado en Florencia, junto con La Gioconda. El italiano argumentó que quería devolverla a su lugar de origen, Italia, pues era Napoleón quien se la había arrebatado. Esto, ciertamente, era falso: la pintura había sido comprada por Francisco I en el siglo XVI. Además, al detenerlo le encontraron una lista de coleccionistas americanos dispuestos a comprar la obra, lo que dejó a la luz sus verdaderas intenciones. Le fue impuesta una pena de 7 meses de cárcel.Aunque la noticia del robo se extendió como la pólvora, poco a poco fue pasando a un segundo plano, pues la Primera Guerra Mundial estaba a punto de estallar. Sin embargo, los periódicos, anuncios, postales y en general, la publicidad, ya se había encargado de hacer de La Gioconda el cuadro más conocido del mundo. El robo de La Mona Lisa es, en mi opinión, la mejor campaña de marketing de la historia.

text: Musée du Louvre in Paris is one of the best and most important museums of the world. It was dedicated to the Impressionism art 🖼 and was open in 1793 and it is the home of La Gioconda by Leonardo Da Vinci. Paris is known as the city 🌃 of lights and this museum is one of its most popular icons as well as the Tuileries Gardens where you can walk and admire the museum from outside which was a palace in old times. If you love art, you cannot miss it! • • Dress 👗 by @sferaofficial • •⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀🇪🇸 El museo de El Louvre en Paris is uno de los más increíbles y más reconocidos a nivel mundial. Está dedicado al arte 🖼 impresionista y fue abierto en 1793, en él está albergado el cuadro de La Gioconda de Leonardo Da Vinci. Paris, conocida como la cuidad 🌃 de las luces, también tiene otros iconos como los jardines de las Tullerias desde donde se puede pasear y admirar al museo, antes un palacio. text: Olhando estas fotos me recordo de quando estava na quinta série estudando sobre os povos da Mesopotamia na disciplina de Educação Artística com o Professor Antonio Rocha. Trata-se do Código de Lei mais antigo do mundo, o Código de Hamurabi, escrito pelo Rei Hamurabi por volta do ano 1772 a.C.Este monumento contém 282 leis escritas em 3600 linhas dispostas em 46 colunas, escritas em escrita cuneiforme, o possível primeiro alfabeto da humanidade.Dentre as leis, se encontra o princípio de Talião o famoso "Olho por Olho, dente por dente", onde, basicamente, a punição para um crime era sofrer aquilo que VC cometeu.Esta peça se encontra na seção sobre a Mesopotamia do Museu do Louvre.#HamurabiCode #codigodehamurabi #Louvre #museedulouvre #louvremuseum #Paris #France  #França #EuroTrip #traveller #backpacking #mochilando

Au bras droit levé, l’index pointé vers le ciel, répond le pied gauche tendu ; au bras gauche plié répond la jambe droite rejetée vers l’arrière. Le dieu, messager de Jupiter porte le pétase ailé, le caducée et repose sur la tête du dieu des vents Eole.👨🏻‍🎨 jean de Boulogne ..#jeandeboulogne #mercure #mythologiegrecque #hermes #hype #art #sculpture #giambologna #museedulouvre #paris

text: No te deseo un regalo cualquiera,te deseo aquello que la mayoría no tiene,te deseo tiempo⏳para reír y divertirte,si lo usas adecuadamente podrás obtener de él lo que quieras.Te deseo tiempo para tu quehacer y tu pensar,no sólo para ti mismo sino también para dedicárselo a los demás.Te deseo tiempo no para apurarte y andar con prisas sino para que siempre estés contento.Te deseo tiempo, no sólo para que transcurra,sino para que te quede tiempo para asombrarte y tiempo para tener confianza y no sólo para que lo veas en el reloj.Te deseo tiempo para que toques las estrellas y tiempo para crecer, para madurar. Para ser tú.Te deseo tiempo, para tener esperanza otra vez y para amar, no tiene sentido añorar.Te deseo tiempo para que te encuentres contigo misma/o, para vivir cada día, cada hora, cada minuto como un regalo.También te deseo tiempo para perdonar y aceptar.Te deseo de corazón que tengas tiempo,tiempo para la vida y para tu vida. –Elli Michler.#time #tiempo #life #enjoylife #livelife #love #travel #paris #museedulouvre #france 🌍❤

name: 2019-09-02 21.56.35 2124070825137837014_museedulouvre.jpg
text: We have been thinking for some time about what our next series will be and, while we still have quite a few to revisit and extend, it is time to introduce a new one!This series will mostly focuses on museums themselves and we will see as they are depicted, through their architecture or their recognizable collections, in paintings and photographs throughout their history.Museums are of course places where we are used to see many artworks and significant objects being exhibited but we often neglect to consider that, as they became home to so many  treasures they could only become worthy artistic subjects themselves.And with this first post we come back to the Louvre where we see Napoleon I visiting the great staircase leading to the most important rooms of the museum (then renamed Napoleon Museum) and being inspecting plans by the main architects.Building this staircase was an important project for Napoleon I who not only commissioned it but also involved himself in many aspects of the architecture and of its many embellishments and decorations. It was finished in 1812 and this painting was made twenty years later by French artist August Couder.Most of the staircase was later destroyed and rebuilt to create what is known today as the Daru staircase leading to the famous Victory of Samothrace. - #Louvre #MuseeduLouvre #LouvreMuseum #Paris #NapoleonMuseum #Napoleon #NapoleonI #AugustCouder #FrenchPainter #19thCenturyArt #19thCentury #Paintings #Museum #Museums #MuseumsinPainting #EscalierDaru #DaruStaircase

text: Mamma et Anna en visite au château 🏰  #chateaudemontal #lot #vacancesenfamille #2septembre #patrimoine #museedulouvre #lajoconde #envadrouille #3945 #histoire #histoiredelart #france #renaissance #peintures#jeannedebalzacPendant la Seconde Guerre Mondiale, les œuvres du Louvre ont été protégées et envoyées dans le sud de la France, les villages de Vayrac, Bétaille ainsi que le château de Montal ont accueilli les plus belles œuvres du musée parisien: œuvres de Véronese, David, de Vinci, etc. Le château de Montal (petit bijou de la Renaissance et restauré à la fin du XIXeme notamment grâce au travail de Rodin) a lui accueilli la Joconde, ce dont les habitants sont très fiers.On peut noter également que Montal est connu pour ses escaliers très travaillés et dont la maquette est exposée au musée de l'Architecture au Trocadéro.

text: back to school time !🤓 . Hello lovelies Today it was an important day for me since I got back to school. I was kinda nervous at first but it was finally really good. My school is huge and I’m already planning everything between work and school. I can’t wait to be a studious bean. I’m reading so many books at the same time actually so I will talk about them when I finish them on my story.📖 . How was your first day of school? If you are not when is your back to school? . Aujourd’hui était un jour super important vu que j’ai repris l’école. J’étais vraiment nerveuse, mais c’était plutôt cool comme première journée. Je vous avoue que mon école est super grande et je suis déjà en train de prévoir comment je vais gérer entre l’école et le travail. J’ai hâte ! En ce moment, je lis beaucoup de livres en même temps, je pense que vous en parlerais en stories quand j’en aurais fini un.📖 . Comment était votre premier jour d’école? Si vous n’avez pas commencé maintenant, quand est ce que vous reprenez les cours? . . .

name: 2019-09-03 01.34.22 2124180436604058618_museedulouvre.jpg
text: The Winged Victory of Samothrace, 190 BC, Grey Lartos marble (boat) with Parian marble (statue), height 3.28 m, Musée du Louvre, Paris. The Winged Victory of Samothrace is one of the masterpieces of Hellenistic sculpture. While the classical Greek concepts, conventions and rules were not entirely abandoned, the artists of the Hellenistic era expanded their formal horizons with dramatic posing, sweeping lines and high contrast of light, shadow and emotions. Experimentation and a sense of freedom allowed the artist to explore his subjects from different unique points of view. The idealism and humility of the classical era were replaced by naturalism and expressions of theatricality, monumentality, energy and power. The Winged Victory is a formidable example of this. It was discovered by Charles Champoiseau and unearthed in 1863 on the Aegean island of Samothrace. The woman represents Nike, the Greek goddess of Victory. She stands on the prow of a ship, bracing the strong wind blowing through her garments. It establishes a sense of eroticism as the dress clings tightly to her body, revealing her breasts and navel through the fabric. The monumental work was placed in a rock niche that had been dug into a hill where it overlooked the theater of the Sanctuary of the Great Gods. It was probably dedicated by the Rhodians in commemoration of a specific naval victory, perhaps the Rhodian victory at Side in 190 BC against the fleet of Antiochus III of Syria. They have found a marble hand and some broken of fingers at the same site which pieced together indicate she must have held it in front of her mouth announcing the victory. The Winged Victory is one of the most famous sculptures in the word and still has an enormous impact and influence on popular culture.Check out my other accounts:@art_questions_and_debates & @my_favorite_work_of_art#sculpture #ancientart #wingedvictory #nikeofsamothrace #ancientsculpture #greekart #hellenistic #nikedisamotracia #victoiredesamothrace #hellenisticart #wingedvictoryofsamothrace #hellenism #hellenisticsculpture #muséedulouvre #greeksculpture #museedulouvre #thewingedvictoryofsamothrace #louvre

text: #paris #museedulouvre # Пирамида Лувра ,подземная часть.Пирамиду 'водрузили' во дворе Наполеона,в самом центре Лувра, к 200летию Французской революции по распоряжению президента Миттерана.Архитектор вдохновился пирамидой Хеопса.Пирамида стала началом Триумфального пути.Если встать к ней спиной,то мы окажемся на одной линии,соединяющей все три Триумфальные Арки через Елисейские поля .Но есть и другая версия,что в создании пирамиды замешаны массоны.А Дэн Браун в своем 'Коде да Винчи' и вовсе 'запрятал' под нее Святой Грааль.

name: 2019-09-03 06.48.40 2124338623311454136_museedulouvre.jpg
text: Le Tombeau de Philippe Pot (15th cent.), Grand Sénéchal of Burgundy and a Knight of the Golden Fleece. My third favorite work at the Louvre.—————————————————-The sculptor is unknown, but it likely that Philippe Pot himself commissioned his own deathbed. He resides on a limestone slab, a sword to his side and lion at his feet, the augurous words of his own instruction in Gothic: “Cy Demorra Messir Philippe Pot”—Here will rest Mr. Philippe Pot. His pallbearers are eight black-robed “pleurants” frozen in time, eternally condemned like Sisyphus to lead this sombre procession for all eternity. —————————————————The history of the tomb post mortem is equally interesting. During the French Revolution, the tomb was seized and sold, then finally ensconced in a French dandy’s presumably creepy country manse in Dijon. After another sale to another French dandy who was fortunate enough not to have been guillotined, the Louvre purchased this wonderful and unique work in 1899. #bourgogne #histoiremedievale #gothgirl #macabre #frenchhistory #senechal #chevalier #museedulouvre #tombeau #parisianstyle #cultofthedead #stolenart #travelswithmyhat #history #europeanhistory #medievalhistory

name: 2019-09-03 10.56.13 2124463218935233764_museedulouvre.jpg
text: King Henri II may have been married to Catherine de Medici but it was Diane de Poitiers that was his one great love. Born on September 3, 1499 to noble parents she would be married off at the age of 15.  Louis de Brézé was 54 years old when he took Diane as his bride. Having two daughters before he would die 17 years after they married, she would spend many years in mourning wearing black. This was when she gravitated towards and adapted Diana, the goddess of the moon and its symbols as her own and wearing black and white representing the dark and light side of the moon for the rest of her life. Becoming the lady in waiting for Francois I wife Queen Claude, the parents of Henri II. They first met when he was still a young boy and remained close, even approving of his marriage to Catherine de Medici when he was only 14. By the age of 15, Henri and the 35 year old Diane began their affair that would last until his death. While Catherine gave birth to 10 children, 3 of which would become king and 2 would become queens, Diane stood alongside. Holding power over Henri and all decision of the court, Catherine had to stand by and could not do a thing. Henri would shower her with jewels, chateaus and art, but it would all end due to a freak accident. On June 30, 1559 he was wounded in a jousting tournament, and would die a few days later. Catherine had her banished from court and had to give up her chateau to the widowed queen. Catherine would then spend much of her time writing the mistress out of history. Covering the Palais des Tuileries with icons of her and Henri and their “great love”. Henri would do the same for Diane long before his wife could. Inside the Musée du Louvre, in the Salle Henri II, each end is marked with the crescent moon, the symbol of Diana. The most amazing monument to Diane is the statue by Jean Goujon in the Louvre. Commissioned by Diane for a fountain at the Château d'Anet. Diane also the goddess of hunters sits with her arm around a large deer. It is stunning to see up close and also featured in another of my favorite pieces in all of the Louvre. More on that later. #dianedepoitiers #paris #parishistoryavecclaudine #museedulouvre #henrii

name: 2019-09-03 17.02.35 2124647621008954860_museedulouvre.jpg
text: 🇵🇹 Deslizei pelas fotos de perfil dos últimos 3 meses. Sinto-me anestesiada. Incrédula. Não me parece real que já tenha terminado a nossa jornada pela Europa. Parece-nos tudo tão distante. Os gelados de limão em Positano. As praias do sul de Itália. Os canais de Veneza e de Amesterdão. O passeio de barco na Suécia e o pôr-do-sol em Santorini. As praias de pedrinhas de Cinque Terre e a vida de Budapeste. As fronteiras da Bulgária e da Macedónia. A família em Praga e a torre Eiffel que acabou de ficar para trás. Foram vários minutos a refletir e bolas... foi do caraças! Obrigada por terem viajado connosco. Que nos dizem da Ásia nos três próximos meses? Estão dentro?.🇬🇧 I’m swiping through the profile photos of the last 3 months. I feel numb. Incredulous. It doesn’t seem real that it is over already, our journey through Europe. It seems so distant. The lemon ice-creams in Positano, the beach in southern Italy, the boat tour in Sweden and the sunset in Santorini. The gravel beaches in Cinque Terra and the life in Budapest. The border between Bulgaria and Macedonia. The family in Prague and the Eiffel Tower that we didn’t get to. Thinking about it.. and it was amazing that’s all I can say! Thank you for having travelled with us. What do you say to Asia in the next three months? Are you in?.#louvre #louvremuseum #louvrepyramid #museedulouvre #paris #parisparis #parisfrance #visitfrance #thisisparis #travelfamily #travelwithlove #fujifilmxpt #backhome #fulltimetravel #choosehappiness #dialysis #dialysislife #kidneypatient

name: 2019-09-03 18.37.10 2124695219313073531_museedulouvre.jpg
text: Да, в Париже очень грязно. Это самая грязнючая европейская столица, где я была.Вдобавок к повсеместно валяющемуся мусору, на всех улицах пованивает мочой (извиняюсь🙊). Такие подтёки и соответствующие ароматы есть даже на здании Лувра😳В Саду Тюильри красивые люди с милыми собачками устраивают пикники. Но ходить по газонам надо аккуратно, т.к. собачьи 💩💩 никто не убирает.Французы плохо говорят по-английский. Считается неуважением, если вы вместо приветствия "Bonjour", сказали стандартное "Hello".С сервисом у них тоже не очень. Цены на топливо, продукты, сувениры и другие вещи в Париже выше, чем в Нидерландах, Бельгии, и, тем более, Германии.А этнический состав здесь кажется таким, что 80-90% местного населения - это граждане из стран Африки👩🏿👵🏾👨🏿👴🏾Но пусть тут у меня будет только красивый Париж💙💚💜Париж - старинный, волшебный, романтичный, город с богатейшей историей и уникальными достопримечательностям💖💖💖

name: 2019-09-03 19.26.10 2124719890040715237_museedulouvre.jpg
text: Minha preferida. #Repost @lets_talk_about_art (@get_repost)・・・The Winged Victory of Samothrace, 190 BC, Grey Lartos marble (boat) with Parian marble (statue), height 3.28 m, Musée du Louvre, Paris. The Winged Victory of Samothrace is one of the masterpieces of Hellenistic sculpture. While the classical Greek concepts, conventions and rules were not entirely abandoned, the artists of the Hellenistic era expanded their formal horizons with dramatic posing, sweeping lines and high contrast of light, shadow and emotions. Experimentation and a sense of freedom allowed the artist to explore his subjects from different unique points of view. The idealism and humility of the classical era were replaced by naturalism and expressions of theatricality, monumentality, energy and power. The Winged Victory is a formidable example of this. It was discovered by Charles Champoiseau and unearthed in 1863 on the Aegean island of Samothrace. The woman represents Nike, the Greek goddess of Victory. She stands on the prow of a ship, bracing the strong wind blowing through her garments. It establishes a sense of eroticism as the dress clings tightly to her body, revealing her breasts and navel through the fabric. The monumental work was placed in a rock niche that had been dug into a hill where it overlooked the theater of the Sanctuary of the Great Gods. It was probably dedicated by the Rhodians in commemoration of a specific naval victory, perhaps the Rhodian victory at Side in 190 BC against the fleet of Antiochus III of Syria. They have found a marble hand and some broken of fingers at the same site which pieced together indicate she must have held it in front of her mouth announcing the victory. The Winged Victory is one of the most famous sculptures in the word and still has an enormous impact and influence on popular culture.Check out my other accounts:@art_questions_and_debates & @my_favorite_work_of_art  #muséedulouvre #greeksculpture #museedulouvre #thewingedvictoryofsamothra
