name: 2019-09-12 00.04.57 2130658414970435233_museedulouvre.jpg
text: 📍 Museu do Louvre: inaugurado a finais do século XVIII, este é o museu mais importante da França é um dos mais visitados em Paris com mais de oito milhões de visitas ao ano.Em 1973 o museu abriu as suas portas com as coleções da monarquia francesa e do Império Naooleonico, mostrando assim um novo conceito de museu dos que na época eram comuns, o qual passava das mãos das clases dirigentes ao desfrute do público em geral.O Louvre, um edifício de 160.000 metros quadrados contém mais de 35.000 obras, as quais são divididas e organizadas de forma temática em diferentes áreas como: antiguidades orientais, egípcias, gregas, romanas, estruscas, história do Louvre, pintura, escultura, objetos de arte, artes gráficas e artes do islã. O museu tem uma das pinturas mais famosas e visitadas do mundo, A Monalisa e a escultura do Vênus de Milo, os quais sem dúvida alguma são os pontos altos da visita.É bom planejar com calma a visita ao museu, pois todos os dias ele reúne milhares de turistas; abre de segunda a domingo, exceto as terças feiras das 09:00 às 18:00. As entradas podem ser compradas online (17,00€) ou na própria bilheteria (15,00€) e para menores de 18 anos a entrada é gratuita! A melhor forma de chegar até lá é de metrô, na estação Palais Royale; de lá existem duas entradas a “principal” que é pela pirâmide de vidro na praça acima do metrô - a qual sempre está cheias de filas, ou no subterrâneo, saindo das catracas do metrô é só seguir as placas e voila, chegar a pirâmide invertida , agora é só comprar o ingresso nas máquinas com cartão de credito ou no balcão com dinheiro! Prepare as pernas para andar MUITO, prepare a câmera para muitas fotos e  se prepare para um dia cheio de aprendizagem!! #travel #travelphotography #travelgram #travelblogger #travelguide #travelholic #travelling #trip #viajem #viaje #viajemais #viagem #viagemperfeita #eurotrip #europatrip #europe_pics #europe_greatshots #francia🇫🇷 #frança🇫🇷 #france_vacations #louvre #louvremuseum #museudolouvre #monalisa #palaisroyale #musee #museedulouvre

name: 2019-09-12 00.30.40 2130671354792454295_museedulouvre.jpg
text: Rembrandt's powerful painting of a butchered ox from 1655 is from a later point in his oeuvre. The strong use of his signature contrasts of light and dark colors as well as the drastic use of the brush are visionary for the time and still inspire artists including myself today. The painting is beautiful and horrible at the same time, triggering many emotions in the spectator. For me it brings back memories of my childhood. Every November at my great grandmother's place in the countryside animals would be butchered. It was a very strong experience for me when I was young. These memories make it possible to not just see but also smell and hear this Rembrandt painting. It is something that engages with all your senses.#RembrandtArtExperience#heikedineguenther #corepainging #rembrandt #inspiration #dutchart #oiloncanvas #baroque #Louvre #museedulouvre #Paris #lightanddark #bull #animalpainting #powerofpaint #basel #swissart #swissartist #visarte

text: The marble statue based on The Source by Jean Ingres and it was formerly on display in @museelouvre. This exhibit was specially commissioned by Dorabji Tata and presented to the Prince of Wales Museum, Mumbai where it is on display.PS: 'The Source' is an oil painting on canvas by French neoclassical painter Jean Ingres. The work was begun in Florence around 1820 and not completed until 1856, in Paris.#thesource #statue #marble #french #neoclassicism #princeofwales #museum #historybuff #mumbai #museedulouvre #nofilter #tbt

(근데 이건 뽕이 맞는 듯)또한 어떤 조직이던지 리더라면 앞장서서 책임감을 갖고 이끌면 좋겠다. 라는 느낌도 받았다...#프랑스 #파리 #france #paris #루브르 #루브르박물관 #louvre #museedulouvre #콜드플레이 #coldplay #vivalavida #여행에미치다 #유디니 #체크인유럽 #유럽 #유럽여행 #travel #travelphotography #여행 #여행사진 #europe #europetravel

text: A few highlights from Musee du Louvre. It took over an hour to get to the Mona Lisa and aside from never having seen her in person before I can't say I would do it again but I'd definitely check out the museum again, it was beautiful. I dont know why I took a picture if the dead fish painting ir any of the other things for that matter, I guess I'm just funny that way. Betchu thought I was going it for the Gram but I'm doing it for my Muva cause she said she wanted to feel like she was with me so 😝#MakingMemories #Londonto Paris  #BlackGirlsTravel #Wanderlust #BlackGirlInParis #MuseeDuLouvre #ArtIsLife #AdventureFeedsMySoul #TravelBug #Filmmaker #DirectHer #ArtFeedsMySoul #FemaleFilmmakers #Explorer  #LifeOfACreative #AdventureAwaits  #SherriesQueendom #TheQuniverse

name: 2019-09-12 14.36.19 2131096982050193033_museedulouvre.jpg
text: The Birthday (c.1915).🎨 Painted by Marc Chagall.Born: 6 July 1887, Liozna, Russian Empire.Died: 28 March 1985, Saint-Paul-de-Vence, France. (aged 97).🖼  Oil on cardboard 81 x 99,7 cm..📝 How Marc Chagall painted his own birthday - inspired by the love and gifts of his muse Bella.."The Birthday” or “Anniversary” as it’s also known, is a 1915 Marc Chagall composition featuring a simple interior typical of Russian provincial tastes of the turn of the 20th century.The woman in the painting is none other than Chagalls’ beloved first wife Bella Rosenfeld whom the artist met in St. Petersburg in 1908.Bella, in a simple black dress is shown tilted forward towards the window as if running, holding a festive bouquet of flowers. Chagall – floating lovingly above her, kissing her with his head bent and twisted, his torso turned away from her. This is an intimate setting, meant for the loved one, and that’s how the viewer gets a feeling of being in the same room as the couple and almost intruding upon an intimate moment. Like so many of Marc Chagall’s other loving tributes to his wife, this painting is filled with intimacy, caring affection, love and warmth.Bella’s own memoirs, written thirty-five years after their first meeting, she recalls how she had managed, with great difficulty, to discover Marc’s date of birth, and visited him on that day, carrying food and flowers in embroidered shawls and Chagall began to paint.In his autobiography “My Life,” Chagall described his first encounter with Bella: “Her silence is mine, her eyes mine. It is as if she knows everything about my childhood, my present, my future, as if she can see right through me.” The color palette is interesting for a different reason. The primary colors in this painting are red, black, white and green – the principal colors used by Kazemir Malevich, the Suprematists and abstractionists of VHUTEMAS. It was the preferred palette for the new century, the new language of Russian modernism.The painting is in the permanent collection of the Museum of Modern Art in New York..(Fig 2, 3, 4 : Details)(Fig 5 : Bella and Marc Chagall in Paris, 1938)...🎂.

name: 2019-09-12 16.35.30 2131156968332992415_museedulouvre.jpg
text: Visiting the Louvre yesterday was absolutely magnificent. I spent nearly six hours there and know that I didn't get to see nearly everything that it has to offer. I read somewhere that if you were to combine the hallways of all three wings of the museum into a single straight line, that line would be eight miles long. The museum has 38,000 works of art displayed throughout 427 rooms. It's astonishing that mankind was able to store and preserve so many ancient artifacts and old pieces of art throughout the course of time...but, of course, it also makes you wonder how many masterpieces and works of literature have been lost along the way due to war and fire. The history behind the Louvre was fascinating as well. At one point on my tour, I overhead a Frenchman tell some guys in English, "This piece of art is not very old...it's only a few hundred years old". One of the men to whom he was speaking replied comedically, "We're Americans...that's very old to us". It was a funny response but so true. The history of America pales in comparison to that of France and other European countries. It's unfathomable to think that people back then were capable of creating such elaborate and well-detailed pieces of art. I definitely hope to one day revisit the Louvre, hopefully when I'll have more time to devote to it the time that it deserves.

It’s a little over lit in the vitrine, but the soft contouring of his facial features and the delicate expression of grief and sorrow are amongst the most beautiful things in 14th century French art. name: 2019-09-12 20.04.04 2131261950158685370_museedulouvre.jpg
text: 🎨 Musée du Louvre 🎨Musée du Louvre merupakan satu museum seni terbesar yang paling banyak dikunjungi dan sebuah monumen bersejarah di dunia. Museum ini bertempat di Istana Louvre (Palais du Louvre) yang awalnya merupakan benteng yang dibangun pada abad ke-12 di bawah pemerintahan Philip II. Sisa-sisa benteng dapat dilihat di ruang bawah tanah museum. Bangunan ini diperluas beberapa kali hingga membentuk Istana Louvre yang sekarang.Museum Louvre terletak di Rive Droite Seine, Arondisemen pertama di Paris Prancis. Hampir 35.000 benda dari zaman prasejarah hingga abad ke-19 dipamerkan di area seluas 60.600 meter persegi ini.Salah satu lukisan yang paling terkenal di seluruh dunia terpajang di sini yakni Mona Lisa.Mona Lisa, adalah lukisan minyak di atas kayu poplar yang dibuat pada abad ke-16. Lukisan ini sering dianggap sebagai salah satu lukisan paling terkenal di dunia dan hanya sedikit karya seni lain yang menjadi pusat perhatian, studi, mitologi, dan parodi.Mahakarya dari pelukis paling berpengaruh di dunia, Leonadro Da Vinci ini sangat terkenal dan sering kali muncul di mana-mana. Lukisan ini dianggap kontroversial karena harganya yang konon katanya mencapai angka 750 Juta US Dollar atau setara 9.7 triliun rupiah.Tak heran jika lukisan ini dipajang dengan pelindung kaca yang tak tembus peluru.Terlihat sederhana namun memukau,belum lagi senyumnya yang misterius.Entah siapa wanita dibalik misteriusnya lukisan Mona Lisa,Yang saya lihat hanya kesan....Kesederhanaan tak akan membuatmu terlihat hina.Yuk kita belajar sederhana sesuai ketentuan Islam.... #Gembelrasakonglomerat#Sipencurimimpi #museedulouvre #monalisa #leonardodavinci #paris🗼 #france🇫🇷#sederhana #kesederhanaantakkanmembuatterlihathina

text: MUSEÉ DU LOUVRE! I saw people physically fighting over selfies with the Mona Lisa (and dared wonder if she is more popular than Beyoncé, who recently spent some time at the Louvre), saw some pieces I thought only existed in art history books, and spent time sketching the cutest little ceramic pieces from Greek Antiquity (some of which were amazingly well preserved!). My advice: go when they’re open late to avoid the crowds. But definitely go. Worth the hype. 😂

name: 2019-09-12 23.56.10 2131378765906198558_museedulouvre.jpg
text: 🇫🇷4️⃣ Paris Jour 4 – Voltamos ao Louvre tentar ver a Monalisa, que não conseguimos ver no primeiro dia pois a fila estava gigante. Não precisamos pagar novo ingresso, pois o Paris Museum Pass não limita o número de visitas. E não é que demos uma baita sorte? Subimos direto até lá, sem fila nenhuma, só um pequeno tumulto bem na frente do quadro, que acredito que sempre exista. O quadro fica dentro de uma proteção de acrílico, longe, e os seguranças pedem para tirar apenas uma foto e logo sair, ou seja, mal pudemos ver! Valeu a pena, claro, mas porque não tinha fila, e aproveitamos pra ver outras partes do museu que não tínhamos visto.Em seguida fomos ao Palays Royal, e tiramos a tarde para conhecer a Rive Gauche (margem esquerda do Rio Sena). Descemos a rua Mouffetard, comemos crepe no Au Ptit Grec (gostamos muito), fomos até o Museu de História Natural conhecer a Galeria da Evolução. Depois pegamos um ônibus até ao Panthéon, onde estão os túmulos de Voltaire, Rousseau, e muitos outros.Depois fomos de Metrô até Galleries Lafayette Haussman, na parte “Le Gourmet” onde estão pequenos quiosques de vários famosos nomes da gastronomia. Comemos um éclair do L’Éclair de Génie, o famoso de caramelo com sal.#paris #roteirospersonalizados #travelplanner #museedulouvre #palaysroyal #monalisa #lajoconde #pantheondeparis #gallerieslafayette

text: #tbt #louvremuseum #museedulouvre #museudoluvre #paris #frança #france🇫🇷 #beleza #arte #rogerscruton #decoração #antiguidades.Reportando-se a Platão, Roger Scruton relembra que o objetivo da arte, seja a poesia, a música ou as artes plásticas, para qualquer pessoa letrada que viveu entre os séculos XVII e XIX, era a busca da Beleza..A partir do século XX, assevera Scruton, a arte deixou de buscar a Beleza e passou a fazer um culto à feiura, além de, por exemplo, ter por objetivo a originalidade a qualquer custo..Para que a arte retome sua trilha, é preciso que ela retorne sua face para a Beleza novamente, tal como fora prescrito pelos filósofos e praticado pelos artistas até então..ROGER SCRUTON E A BELEZA COMO VALOR UNIVERSALpor André Assi Barreto. Artigo publicado em 01.11.2017

name: 2019-09-13 04.14.02 2131508553391900050_museedulouvre.jpg
text: "Nike di Samotracia", Pitocrito, II secolo a.C., Museo del Louvre, Parigi•L'opera venne scolpita a Rodi in epoca ellenistica per commemorare la vittoria della lega delio-attica nella battaglia dell'Eurimedonte. Dopo esser rimasta nel santuario dei Grandi Dei di Samotracia per diversi secoli, la "Nike" scomparve misteriosamente, per poi essere rinvenuta il 15 aprile 1863 in stato frammentario da Charles Champoiseau, viceconsole francese a Edirne, nella stessa isola egea.La statua fu acquistata dai francesi, che la inclusero nelle collezioni del Museo del Louvre. Da cui venne spostata solo una volta nel 1939, quando per proteggerla dall'imminente seconda guerra mondiale venne trasportata nel castello di Valençay.•••#telemachus #arte #cultura #nikedisamotracia #nike #pitocrito #statua #scultura #louvre #parigi #paris #museedulouvre #sculpture #marble

text: Dynamic Symmetry IBalance is one of the easier elements of composition to see, and you'll soon discover whether your natural inclination is towards a perfectly balanced or symmetrical composition or an unbalanced, asymmetrical one. It's not that one is better than the other, but whichever you choose as the underlying component of your composition has an impact on the overall feeling of the finished painting. Symmetrical tends to feel calmer and asymmetrical livelier.#composition #symmetry_art #lajoconde #photography #photographer #people #tableau #art#louvre #museedulouvre #pictureoftheday #picture #peinture

name: 2019-09-13 14.58.58 2131833165292118536_museedulouvre.jpg
text: Лувр, один из символов Парижа. Бывшая крепость, Лувр стал одной из красивейших резиденций королей Франции. Постепенно появляется проект превратить здание Лувра в музей. 10 августа 1793 года двери музея Наполеона (так назывался Лувр во время 1й империи) были впервые открыты для публики.Коллекция Лувра уникальна. Она включает шедевры и экспонаты разных периодов, культур, цивилизаций.Оценить и познакомиться со всей коллекцией за один визит, я считаю, невозможно (но можно иметь общее представление). Это то место, куда нужно постоянно возвращаться. Многие известные художники ходили за вдохновением в Лувр. Для меня поход в музей-это, как арт терапия. Прикоснуться к прекрасному, помечтать, поразмышлять, замедлиться, обновиться, узнать много нового. Однажды я прибыла к открытию и быстро рванула в зал с греческими статуями. Наедине с прекрасными творениями, в тишине, утренние лучи солнца освещали зал. Это незабываемо...Желающих попасть в Лувр всё больше и больше (10 млн в год). Последний мой визит в Лувр напоминал визит в Ватикан. Стало меньше интимности и спонтанности. Визит нужно планировать заранее, билеты покупать онлайн. Или искать информацию, когда двери музея открываются для всех желающих бесплатно. Желаю всем приятного визита и времяпровождения. PS : 21 и 22го сентября во Франции проходит выходной культурного наследия. Двери многих закрытых в остальное время заведений, будут открыты для посещения. #франция, #париж, #любимый город, #прогулка по Парижу, #лувр, #искусство, #paris, #Paris, #parisienne, #museedulouvre, #france .

name: 2019-09-13 19.54.47 2131982055324669730_museedulouvre.jpg
text: .[🚨Travaux de la Salle des États] _🕰Édifiée par Lefuel, la salle des États était destinée à accueillir, à partir de 1859, les grandes séances législatives sous Napoléon III. Rattachée au musée en 1878, elle perd son décor allégorique et abrite la peinture française du 19e siècle. Elle accueille aujourd’hui les chefs-d’oeuvre de la peinture vénitienne mais aussi la célèbre Joconde._🔵À sa réouverture au grand public en octobre 2019, la salle sera habillée d’une nouvelle couleur, dévoilée hier sur les réseaux sociaux du @museelouvre . Ce bleu-nuit saura, j’en suis certain, remplacer avec succès l’ancien « beige » fatigué et magnifier les œuvres accrochées dans cette célèbre salle 711.__________Aile DenonSalle des États Salle 711 __________📷La salle en mars 2018©️InsideTheLouvre / @n.bousser __________#louvre #louvremuseum #museedulouvre #art #architecture #culture #museum #paris #france🇫🇷 #salledesÉtats #patrimoinefrancais #insta #instagram #instatravel #travel #trip #palace #museum #museum #architecture #lefuel #peinture #arthistory #historyofart #patrimoinefrancais #joconde

name: 2019-09-13 19.58.43 2131984035932171562_museedulouvre.jpg
text: Organized by @thanksfor.nothing , free and accessible to all, the aim of this conference is to think about the links between artistic practice and citizen action, by presenting innovative initiatives from committed actors in the world of art, academics and associations. The event brings together artists, gallerists, philosophers, journalists and association leaders among others on September 20, 2019 at Musée du Louvre, Paris.With the Presidents and representatives of the associations supported: Anafé, Primo Levi, The Cimade, Migreurop, Thot Center. As well as the protagonists of the project: Chantal Crousel and Niklas Svennung, Chantal Crousel Gallery. In partnership with the Louvre Museum and the New York Times, the Société Générale, Sciences Po, The Art Newspaper, Madame Figaro and Numéro..Image: Chantal Crousel & Niklas Svennung. Photo: Sebastiano Pellion di Persano.#Thanksfornothing #Wedream #Talk #GalerieChantalCrousel #museeduLouvre #Paris

name: 2019-09-13 23.12.38 2132081636221448879_museedulouvre.jpg
text: There’s a great little exhibition up on the second floor of Sully about FRAMES. The museum is obviously jam-packed with masterpieces but the frames themselves can also be considered as works of art in their own right. ⠀Ever wondered how a frame changes the way you perceive a painting? Here’s a wonderful still life by Chardin. The frame, executed later than the painting itself, is *relatively* simple, echoing the balanced simplicity of Chardin’s composition.⠀.⠀.⠀.⠀Jean-Siméon Chardin⠀Pipes et vases à boire, or La Tabagie⠀c. 1737⠀Oil on canvas⠀Sully wing, room 905⠀.⠀Louis XVI style frame⠀c. 1760 - 1770⠀.⠀Exhibition, “Regards sur les cadres”, until November 3rd 2019⠀Sully wing, second floor, rooms 904-906...#louvre #louvremuseum #museedulouvre #painting #frames #chardin #jeansimeonchardin #stilllife #18thcentury #expo #exhibition #tabagie #getyoursmokeon #ceciestunepipe #cecinestpasunepipe #paris #france #france🇫🇷 #patrimoine #regardssurlescadres #youvebeenframed

text: 🇫🇷 Le vendredi c’est #LaModeAuLouvre !-🖋Aujourd’hui, attardons-nous sur l’élégance de Baldassare Castiglione, poète, humaniste et ambassadeur du duc d'Urbin, avec qui Raphaël s’était lié d’amitié.-🔎Raphaël représente Castiglione dans un costume discret, coiffé d'un turban enserrant la chevelure sur lequel s'ajuste un béret à bords découpés et orné d'une médaille, enveloppé d'un pourpoint sombre garni d'une fourrure grise retenue par un ruban noir, ouvert sur une chemise blanche bouffante.-❄️Cette tenue hivernale permet de supposer que le portrait fut peint pendant l'hiver 1514-1515 lorsque Castiglione, chargé par le duc d'Urbin d'une ambassade auprès du pape Léon X, se trouvait à Rome, où Raphaël était actif depuis 1508.- 👁 L'harmonie sobre de ce costume, contenue entre le noir, le gris et le blanc, se prolonge dans le fond du portrait, d'un gris beige clair et chaud, concentrant l'attention du spectateur sur le visage et son intense regard bleu.- - - - 🌍 It’s #FashionFriday at the Louvre!- 🖋Today, let’s focus on the elegance of Baldassare Castiglione, poet, humanist, and ambassador, whom Raphael first met as a young man in Urbino.-🔎Castiglione is depicted in a discret costume. The ambassador's hair is wrapped in a turban over which sits a beret with a notched edge adorned with a medallion; his sober doublet is trimmed in gray fur laced with black ribbon; under it, a bloused white shirt.-❄️This winter dress suggests that the portrait was painted during the winter of 1514–1515 when Castiglione, appointed by the Duke of Urbino to Pope Leo X, was in Rome. Raphael had been working there since 1508.- 👁The sober harmony of the costume, limited to shades of black, gray and white, is extended in the painting's background of a light and warm gray-beige tone, deliberately focusing the viewer's attention on the face and the intense gaze. - 📷 © RMN - Grand Palais (Musée du Louvre) / Tony Querrec . . . #Louvre #MuseeDuLouvre

Pero no; no te quiero.A veces es tan sencillo como ignorar tu aliento,en otras ocasiones requiere derrumbar pensamientos;la mayoría de las veces lluevo para calmar tu tormenta. name: 2019-09-14 01.35.05 2132153327076288327_museedulouvre.jpg
text: Музей Лувра — один из крупнейших и самый популярный художественный музей мира. В нем хранится🖼️ «Мона Лиза», или «Джоконда» — картина Леонардо да Винчи, одно из самых известных произведений живописи! Чтобы полюбоваться ей мы отстояли 3 очереди!!! 🤪Это заняло не менее 30 минут, а на изучение картины дают 30 секунд!!!! 🤷‍♀️Так же здесь представлена знаменитая статуя богини любви Афродиты из белого мрамора «Венера Милосская» — древнегреческая скульптура, созданная приблизительно между 130 и 100 годами до нашей эры. 🗿 И ещё много других шедевров разных времен 🏺🎨#лувр #музейлувр #Louvre #MuseeduLouvre #монализа #франция #париж

name: 2019-09-14 04.28.36 2132240662954059470_museedulouvre.jpg
text: 두려워 했었다. 그때 그 느낌이 다시 들까봐.⠀학생적 역사 수업에서 들었던 이야기들. 그때 슬라이드로만 봤던 작품들을 처음 실물로 접했을때 솟구쳐 오르는 흥분감, 이어 내 상상 속에서 펼쳐지던 황홀한 무용담. 자크-루이 다비드의 호라티 형제 이야기. 들라크루아의 청녹색 포화 가운데 빛나던 삼색기. 제리코의 흑인 노예가 포착한 암흑속 희망.⠀그리고 전 세계에서 찾아온 수많은 젊은이들. 사방으로 들려오는 그들의 속삭임과 웃음. 그런 그들도 모나리자 앞에선 숨을 죽였다. 서로의 이름은 모르지만 이때만큼은 우리사이의 간극이 사라져버린 듯했다.⠀기억에 새겨진 그날을 이따금 애청곡같이 찾으며 아려오는 마음을 달래곤 했었다.⠀오늘, 그때의 감상은 다시 찾아왔고 난 새벽잠을 설친다. 안티클라이막스가 언제나 허망한 법이지만 인생이 외롭고 공허하다는 생각에 편치가 않다. 금의환향 하는 오딧세우스처럼 내 마음속 판테온으로 영원히 돌아가고 싶다. 참을수 없는 존재의 가벼움의 토마쉬같이 사랑하는 이들과 함께 귀농하여 영원회귀하는 자연에 여생을 맡길까. ⠀

text: .Vênus e as Graças Surpreendidas por um Mortal.Jacques Blanchard - c. 1632Museu do Louvre, Paris, França Movimento: Barroco.📝📝📝Nesta pintura, com a sua pouca habitual combinação de elementos, um homem observa a deusa e as suas companheiras sem pudor e nenhuma das mulheres se retrai modestamente diante do homem. As suas atitudes naturais e a sua beleza despida fazem do amor sensual e físico o tema desta pintura. As obras de Blanchard foram e são muito populares, principalmente por causa do seu extraordinário tratamento da nudez feminina e do seu agradável uso da cor..#️⃣#️⃣#️⃣#jacquesblanchard #blanchard #barroco #museedulouvre #pintura #pinturafrancesa #cult #cultura #art #arte #historiadaarte #historiadelarte #arthistory #storiadellarte #cult_artes #traveling_arte #1632.💬💬💬

name: 2019-09-14 13.44.24 2132520404242531294_museedulouvre.jpg
text: PARIS🇫🇷 #2⠀#루브르박물관 #Louvre미술을 잘 모르는 나조차 온 사방에 펼쳐진친숙한 작품들에 감탄이..🤭⠀'민중을 이끄는 자유의 여신'의 분위기에 압도당하고,'사모트라케의 니케', '밀로의 비너스'의 섬세함과'루이14세의 초상' 까지 미술책 안에 들어온 기분이였다.'모나리자'는 기나긴 관람객 줄에 기대 가득했지만사진 한장 찍고 지나갈 때 너무 허무했다.⠀향하는 곳 마다 작품들이 가득해서나올 수 없는 개미지옥이였던 루브르.반의 반도 보지 못하고 나와 아쉬움이 가득했다.꼭 한번 다시 오고 싶은 공간!

text: De tout, il resta trois choses : La certitude que tout était en train de commencer, la certitude qu’il fallait continuer,la certitude que cela serait interrompu avant que d’être terminé. Faire de l’interruption, un nouveau chemin, faire de la chute, un pas de danse, faire de la peur, un escalier, du rêve, un pont, de la recherche…une rencontre. name: 2019-09-14 17.40.39 2132639319329162349_museedulouvre.jpg
text: Seeing this work in person was a hard experience: being herded at haste in a crowd through rooms of work I would very much have wanted to stand and admire. Hard, too, was seeing the rest of the wing she resides in filled with paintings and largely empty. This is the only image of the Mona Lisa that I took and I am satisfied that it begins to accurately display the real experience of seeing her. #thelouvre #themonalisa #art #museedulouvre #artappreciation

text: 2019.09.05 坐著等轉機回台北的空檔 (結果只打完一部分)除了跟同事家人好友亂聊之外仔細回想並慢慢品味著這趟 traveling 所帶來的衝擊與感動很多事情你沒有親自下去做親身去體驗人家講再多都是別人的感受譬如說我娘最擔心的扒手跟安全的問題在南法待了6天 包括 馬賽兩天在巴黎待了6天幾乎每天都玩到晚上12點甚至一點才回到hotel不管是在街頭, 地鐵, 公車上都不曾感受到有人有接近試圖偷扒搶竊的意圖當然包包全程上鎖隨時注意四周狀況尤其後方的動靜這是我打從看完mission impossible後就內建的反射反應(對～就是那個第一集湯姆在餐廳講完話把炸彈口香糖用力扔甩年上水族箱的那一幕)(ㄜ , 好像透露了年紀!!!XD)所以這將近18天旅程唯一丟掉的東西就是一個備用的鎖頭(而且應該是掉在英國的hotel裡才是 -> 習慣的建立真的是最難的部分)當然還有很多的感受 有空再來分享——————————————————————————— #旅遊 #自拍#景點#夜景#巴黎#歐洲#法國#旅行者#羅浮宮 #法國巴黎#歐洲旅遊#法國旅遊#環遊世界 #france#Louvre #selfie#paris#travel#travelgram#traveller#love_night#travelblogger#museedulouvre#travelaroundtheworld #travelling_europe#nightview #nightvision

name: 2019-09-15 02.05.41 2132893508814632624_museedulouvre.jpg
text: Il sorriso di Monna Lisa ✨🖼..In seguito a uno studio eseguito da un team di scienziati è stato riscontrato che il sorriso di Monna Lisa è asimmetrico. Si sono sviluppate diverse teorie a proposito, ma finora la più accreditata è che Leonardo avesse accentuato volontariamente quel particolare innaturale per comunicare qualcosa attraverso la sua opera. Il sorriso di Monna Lisa di fatto non c’è, tuttavia si percepisce: è tutto racchiuso nell’enigma degli occhi. Il suo viso sembra evocare una sorta di felicità spirituale, interiore. In questa espressione misteriosa, quasi indecifrabile, risiede l’inestimabile bellezza di un capolavoro che, nei secoli, non ha mai cessato di interrogare osservatori provenienti da ogni parte del mondo. 🎨..#louvre #museedulouvre #lagioconda #leonardodavinci #monnalisa #monalisasmile #louvremuseum #unavitaletteraria #lavieparisienne #paris #parisienne #art #painting #poetry #poetrylife

name: 2019-09-15 02.34.05 2132907804519091375_museedulouvre.jpg
text: L’arch de Triomphe du Carrousel was originally topped with the quadriga (4 horse racing chariot) stolen (or “acquired”) by Napoleon from St. Mark’s in Venice.  The sculpture was returned upon the restoration of the Bourbons and a replacement sculpture was put in it’s place.  The chariot is driven by Peace and flanked by victory on each side.  I’m sure it’s the most ornate middle finger ever given.#paris #jardindetuileries #tuileries #museedulouvre #historicaxis #historicaxisofparis #triumphalarch #triumphalway #napoleon #bourbons #restoration #francoisfredericlemot #lemot #sculpture #proverbialmiddlefinger

name: 2019-09-15 03.20.53 2132931356770936975_museedulouvre.jpg
text: パリ到着日は、2007年以降最大のストライキの日！当然、乗るはずだった地下鉄は動かず、どうにか一番近いだろう駅まで動いている列車で向かう。そこから徒歩約30分、荷物をガラガラ引いてホテルへ。アンラッキーな日にも小さな幸せを探すことは大事ですね。地下を通っていたら見られなかっただろう街並みや、建物。ストライキを体感すること自体なかなかない経験だと思うので、軽くパニックしましたが貴重な体験をしました。この日行きたかった場所にも、予定通りなんとか行けた！タクシーを捕まえたり、一時的に動いていた地下鉄に乗ったり。まずは必ず見たかったカタコンベ。想像より広く、とにかく骨の世界でした。そしてルーブル美術館。モナリザはやはり大人気で、30分以上は並びました。ミロのヴィーナスも見て、目標達成しました！帰りも最寄り駅は閉鎖されていて、また仕方なく徒歩…それでも途中で素敵なフランス料理店を見つけたりと、なんだかんだ良い思い出になった日でした。#france #paris #france🇫🇷 #catacombs #catacombesdeparis #catacombsofparis #louvre #louvremuseum #museedulouvre #strike #フランス #パリ #カタコンベ #カタコンブドパリ #ルーブル美術館 #ルーブル #ストライキ

name: 2019-09-15 14.14.39 2133260402847631430_museedulouvre.jpg
text: 💝🖼 Jean-Antoine Watteau, Pilgrimage to the Isle of Cythera, 1717, 🏛 @museelouvre Jean-Antoine Watteau (1684 – 1721) was the most influential French painter of the 18th century. His invention of fête galantewas ingenious. His use of vibrant colours was inspirational. His use of bold brushstrokes was daring. Watteau’s style influenced French painters throughout the 18th and 19th centuries. His themes of courtship, falling in love, and love’s triumph are magnificently fused together in Pilgrimage to the Isle of Cythera. This is a Watteau masterpiece. This is a Rococo romance.More 📜 Dailyartmagazine.com (link in a bio) ✍ James W. Singer #art #arthistory #historyofart #arte #kunst #artist #painting #paintings #rococo #museedulouvre #louvre #watteau #frenchart #fineart #instaart #artgallery #oilpainting #artwork #artworks #masterpiece #culture

name: 2019-09-15 14.30.28 2133268368971739337_museedulouvre.jpg
text: 📖« Mais il est beau de dos, il regarde peu les murs, avance au milieu de la galerie Denon. Je devine quel effort c’est de chercher en lui ce qu’il demeure de l’intérêt de vivre: l’art est ce qui rend la vie plus intéressante que l’art. » Josselin Guillois - Louvre - @editionsduseuil📋Je me suis beaucoup demandé comment j’allais parler de ce livre. Faut-il d’abord évoquer sa construction? Le journal intime de trois femmes. Marcelle, Carmen, Jeanne. Journal intime ou journal d’une intimité féminine, corporelle et amoureuse poussée à son paroxysme. Faut-il plutôt admirer l’homme qui se dessine héroïquement dans l’ombre de ces trois femmes? Jacques Jaujard, directeur des musées nationaux. L’homme qui fit voyager Mona et tous les autres pour les sauver de la haine nazie. Faut-il, à l’instar de Jeanne, dresser l’inventaire de tous ces noms de peintres qui forment à eux seuls une musique réconfortante et envoûtante?Faut-il surtout engager un débat sur l’art, sa désacralisation, son émancipation, son pouvoir à offrir sens et beauté à la vie du regardeur? Quand bien même je vous aurais dit tout ça, je ne vous aurais pas tout dit, car dans ce premier roman de Josselin Guillois, ces histoires, l’Histoire se surimpriment toutes les unes aux autres, dans une danse qui mêle le sacré, le prosaïque, l’humour et la poésie. C’est un ravissement, consenti et assumé. - Louvre - promet une visite singulière. #josselinguillois#louvre#roman#seuil#lire#livre#instalivre#avislecture#book#bookstagram#litteraturefrancaise#rentreelitteraire2019#litterature#lecture#lecturedumoment#livreaddict#instabooks#livresque#lecturepassion#passionlivres#museedulouvre#paris#joconde#monalisa#jacquesjaujard#jeanneboitel#art#peinture#resistance

text: ✅19.08.17✅.오늘은 세계 3대 박물관 중 하나인 #루브르박물관 (Louvre Museum)을 방문했습니다😻.박물관으로 사용되고 있는 현재의 건물은 원래 루브르 #궁전 이었습니다.😀.1682년 루브르 궁전에서 박물관으로 탈바꿈하였는데요, 그 이유는 루이 14세가 처소🏠를 베르사유 궁전으로 옮기면서라고 합니다..루브르 박물관하면 제일 떠오르는 것은 바로✨ 유리 피라미드죠..!👏🏻👏🏻.중국계 미국인 건축인인 I.M.Pei에 의해 설치되었으며 이 구조는 과거와 🔛미래를 투명하게 연결한다는 의미라고 합니다😊.박물관 내에는 현재 38만점의 예술품이 소장되어 있다고 하는데,,,🙊 정말 놀랍지 않나요❓..🇫🇷제일 유명한 작품인 <#모나리자 >를 비롯한 <#사모트라케의니케 >, <#민중을이끄는자유의여신 >등을 직접 볼 수 있어 감회가 새로웠던 시간이었습니다!❤️...#서울여자대학교 #서울여대 #세계문화체험과리더십 #세문리 #1기 #5g팀 #18학번 #동기들 #louvremuseum #루브르 #박물관 #museedulouvre #france #프랑스 #파리여행 #여행10일차 #좋아요 #선팔 #맞팔 #데일리 #일상스타그램 #instagram #instadaily #travelphotography #여행스타그램

name: 2019-09-15 21.59.18 2133494272087969062_museedulouvre.jpg
text: Paris is a famous city for many things! And one of my favorite thing are Parisian gardens. 🌺💕 The architecture, flowers, and the perfect relaxing mood 🧘🏻‍♀️This picture was taken in the Tuileries garden, most famous Parisian garden. That’s the one in front of the Louvre 🗼 - Aleksandra 🍒..Paris est une ville connue pour plusieurs choses! Mais mes endroits favoris sont sûrement les jardins et les parcs 🌺💕 L’architecture, les fleurs, la végétation et cette ambiance détente 🧘🏻‍♀️Cette photo a été prise aux tuileries, le jardin parisien sûrement le plus connu, car c’est celui en face du Louvre 😉🗼...#paris #garden #parisian #parisgarden #louvre #museedulouvre #jardinlouvre #tuileries #jardindestuileries #parisianlife #parisianlifestyle #frenchgarden #frenchpark #polishgirl #retro #retrogirl #vintagelover #vintage #vintageclothes #parisiangirl #visitparis #parisfamousplace #parislouvre #parislover  #france #influenceuse #l4l  #vintagestyle #80s #70s

name: 2019-09-15 22.00.22 2133494815225241944_museedulouvre.jpg
text: When you live in Paris the greatest thing is taking walks after a long day for work, near the famous places like the Louvre or the Eiffel Tower. You can appriciate beautiful architectures while the sun sets. ☀️ It’s not always easy to live in such a busy town, but we are happy to have theses special places which reminds us the beauty of our place 💕..Lorsqu’on vit à Paris la meilleure chose est pouvoir faire une petite balade après une longue journée de travail près d’endroits célèbres comme le Louvre ou la Tour Eiffel. On peut apprécier la beauté de l’architecture française en contemplant le soleil couchant. ☀️ Il n’est pas toujours facile de vivre dans une ville active, mais nous sommes heureux d’avoir ces superbes endroits qui nous comblent de bonheur 💕...#Louvre #paris #parisianlife #parisianlifestyle #museedulouvre #louvreparc #tuileries #jardindestuileries #garden #park #gardeninparis #parisgarden #nature #natureincity #famousplaceinparis #france #frencharchitecture #frenchgarden #renaissance #sculpture #art #statue #sunset #paysage #pinksky #bluesky #l4l #l4likes #parisiangarden #parisian

text: Never would I have ever thought that the Paris museum pass would have given me the most precious experience on this Europe trip. It was like living in the social studies and history textbooks LIVE in action. I have gained so much more appreciation from the renaissance sculptures to the impressionistic modern art, from the works of painters like Van Gogh, Picasso, da Vinci, to Monet, was just mind blowing. I am sure the impact has already made me see things differently and having to study and understand the deeper meaning of these great art works will definitely shape me to become a better person and a better musician.#paris #museum #museumpass #europe #trip #socialstudies #history #renaissance #impressionism #vangogh #picasso #davinci #monet #musician #museedulouvre #mussedorsay

On retrouve de l'or dans chacune des pièces : du salon à la salle à manger..J'ai eu un immense coup de cœur pour cette partie du musée..Et vous, vous etes déjà allé au musée du Louvre ? Qu'est-ce qui vous a marqué ?.Merci encore à @odyssee_euralens2019 pour l'organisation de la journée, à @porte_mine ainsi qu'au @museelouvre pour son excellent accueil. .Bonne soirée 😘.#frenchy #frenchgirl #paris #musee #museedulouvre #museelouvre #museelouvreparis #louvre #loveparis #huaweip20 #p20photography #huawei #huaweishot #napoleon3 #appartementnapoleoniii #appartementnapoleon3 #france #visitfrance #paris_tourisme #paristourisme #tourismeParis #paris #parisjetaime #parislove #girltraveler #girltravel

text: This serie of portraits should be called "The One Eyebrow That Was Bigger Than The Other" 😂I do not have any philosophical thoughts today but simply something that has nothing to do with the photo..It's my first getting back home alone at night in Paris and I was scared the whole way which pretty much sucked. I hate that feeling of being unsafe and vulnerable in the streets and as @emmawatson want to fight for a world in which women feel safe outside. Let's hope but also fight together. Im glad to have made this YouTube video in which I talk more about this fight we could do together 💪.#louvre #photoshootlouvre #photoslouvre #parisblogger #agirlinparis #abloggerinParis #womenwhotraveltheworld #womenfightfortheirrights #museedulouvre #fashioninspired #styleinspo #styleinspired #fashionblogger #outfitsideas #coldweatheroutfits

name: 2019-09-16 16.51.31 2134064138731835852_museedulouvre.jpg
text: By the Canal..🎨 Painted by Wilhelm von Gegerfelt.Born: 9 November 1844, Gothenburg, Sweden.Died: 2 April 1920, Torekov, Sweden..🖼 Oil on canvas 65 x 93 cm..📝 Born in Gothenburg, Gegerfelt was the son the architect Victor von Gegerfelt (1817-1915)From 1861 to 1863, he studied at the Royal Danish Academy, at the Royal Swedish Academy from 1864 to 1867, and thereafter in Düsseldorf until 1872.He then went to Paris where he developed a new technique joining Alfred Wahlberg as one of the first Swedes to represent the Modern Breakthrough in Nordic art. He travelled to the north coast of France, to Italy and to England, painting landscapes of Venice's lagoons and the English chalk cliffs, in addition to scenes of summer evenings in Sweden.His works can be seen in the National Museum in Stockholm, in the Gothenburg Museum of Art and in Skagens Museum.Gegerfelt exhibited in Monaco from 1883 and won a silver medal at the Vienna exhibition the same year. In Paris, he sold his paintings to the Duke of Bassano as well as to Goupil & Cie.Gagerfelt spent his later life in the fishing village of Torekov in the south of Sweden..(Fig 2, 3, 4: Details)...#museum #moma #metmuseum #museedulouvre #britishmuseum #nationalgallery #museodelprado #vangoghmuseum #brooklynmuseum #artforum #artbasel #tatemodern #instamuseum #rijksmuseum #whitneymuseum #nationalgalleryofvictoria #nationalmuseum #gettymuseum #curator #graffiti #streetart #oilpainting #artwork #landscape #boat #wilhelmvongegerfelt #gothenburg #torekov #sweden #yourarttimes

name: 2019-09-16 20.06.54 2134162468184890578_museedulouvre.jpg
text: Ils sont quatre autour d’une table. Une table de jeu où l’on joue gros : les pièces sur la table en témoignent. Mais tout n’est pas aussi clair que l’or des mises. Les regards en coin des femmes sont suffisamment équivoques pour que l’on soit bien certain qu’il n’y a pas que l’homme qui soit dans le coup, tirant d’un air détaché un as de carreau  de sa ceinture. Seul le garçon assis à droite n’y voit que du feu. Son regard benêt, son vêtement trop riche le signalent comme la victime idéale de cette bande de voleurs. Son vêtement est une splendeur d’argent, de broderies et de rubans. Naïf tout à son jeu, il ne devine rien… La lumière éclaire le dos du tricheur, éclairant ses cartes cachées et laissant son visage dans l’ombre.D’une main, la servante apporte un verre de vin clair, de l’autre elle porte une bouteille entourée de jonc.La femme assise au centre est habillée d’une riche robe de velours à très large décolleté, ornée de crevés sur les manches  et une toque ornée d’une plume. Elle porte de nombreux bijoux, en particulier des perles. De sa main droite, elle semble s’adresser au tricheur, qui ne voit pas son geste.  Le détail de ces quatre mains met en évidence l’harmonieuse composition du tableau où chaque détail a sa place. Les mains des complices se trouvent ainsi rapprochées, comme pour insister sur leur connivence. Dans la palette de couleurs, les peaux sont très blanches, les rouges variés sont mis en valeur par les nuances de beiges. Cette huile sur toile de 1635 est exposée au musée du Louvre.#georgesdelatour #frenchart #frenchartist #apprendreavoir #histoiredesarts #latour #baroque #museedulouvre #artfrancais #artistefrancais #gambling #jeu #delatour #tricheur #tricheurs #tabledejeu #tabledejeux #joueursdecartes #vin #wine #ruban #rubans #plume #plumes #mains #handsinart #salledejeux #arthistoryforkids #ombreetlumiere #ombre

name: 2019-09-17 04.45.31 2134423509141501963_museedulouvre.jpg
text: The Louvre has over 9000 frames in its collections 😮⁠⠀It's often hard to find out about the frames which adorn and support the paintings in a museum. Some frames were chosen by the artists themselves, some are testament to the tastes of art collectors over the years and some have been chosen by different generations of museum curators. ⁠⠀The little exhibition "Regards sur les cadres" at the Louvre sheds light on the framing of paintings and on how to recognise different styles. Here are some examples of French 18th century.⁠⠀.⁠⠀.⁠⠀.⁠⠀Louis XVI style frames⁠⠀1760 - 1780⁠⠀Sully wing, room 904⁠⠀.⁠⠀.⁠⠀.⁠⠀#louvre #louvremuseum #expo #exhibition #frames #museum #museedulouvre #paris #france #france🇫🇷 #instatravel #instatravelling #louisxvi #louisxvistyle #18thcentury #youvebeenframed #regardssurlescadres

name: 2019-09-17 05.22.46 2134442258737414067_museedulouvre.jpg
text: .[📍Le Louvre méconnu / La salle des icônes grecques et russes] _Au premier étage de l’aile de Flore, en fond de Grande Galerie, sont exposées les icônes grecques et russes, noyées dans les collections de peintures espagnoles. Rares sont ceux qui parviennent jusqu’à l’intimiste écrin que constitue la salle 734. Y sont visibles des chefs-d’œuvre, à commencer par la célèbre Vierge géorgienne._________La Vierge géorgienne (dite), Vierge et l'EnfantRussie centrale XVIe siècle_🕰Cette représentation de la Vierge, la main droite levée pour désigner l'Enfant posé sur son bras gauche, dérive du type byzantin de la Vierge hodigitria ("celle qui montre le chemin") dont de nombreuses variantes populaires ont existé en Russie.____________Aile Denon1er étage Salle 734____________📷©️InsideTheLouvre / @n.bousser ____________l#ouvre #museedulouvre #louvremuseum #art #culture #painting #icône #vierge #viergegéorgienne #russie #grèce #portrait #paris #france #france🇫🇷 #greek #work #insta #instagram #instatravel #instatrip #travel #trip #instatraveling #patrimoine #chefdoeuvre

name: 2019-09-17 05.49.20 2134455622435997228_museedulouvre.jpg
text: .[📍Le Louvre méconnu / La salle des icônes grecques et russes] _Au premier étage de l’aile de Flore, en fond de Grande Galerie, sont exposées les icônes grecques et russes, noyées dans les collections de peintures espagnoles. Rares sont ceux qui parviennent jusqu’à l’intimiste écrin que constitue la salle 734. Y sont visibles des chefs-d’œuvre, à commencer par la célèbre Vierge géorgienne.____________Ici /La Vierge et l'Enfant entre saint Cyriaque et saint Georges Peintre crétoisTroisième quart du XVe siècle (?)_🕰Cette icône de dimensions imposantes (H. : 0,94 m. ; L. : 1,13 m.) représente au centre la Vierge en pied avec l'Enfant (selon le type de la Nikopoia), encadrée à sa droite par saint Cyriaque, évêque de Jérusalem, et à sa gauche par saint Georges, revêtu de son armure avec la lance et le bouclier. Le style de cette icône présente une parenté avec celui d'Andreas Ritzos (1421 - 1492), un des plus grands peintres crétois du XVe siècle____________Aile Denon1er étage Salle 734____________📷©️InsideTheLouvre / @n.bousser ____________l#ouvre #museedulouvre #louvremuseum #art #culture #painting #icône #vierge #viergegéorgienne #russie #grèce #portrait #paris #france #france🇫🇷 #greek #work #insta #instagram #instatravel #instatrip #travel #trip #instatraveling #patrimoine #chefdoeuvre

text: The Louvre Pyramid (Pyramide du Louvre) is a large glass and metal pyramid designed by Chinese-American architect I. M. Pei, surrounded by three smaller pyramids, in the main courtyard (Cour Napoléon) of the Louvre Palace (Palais du Louvre) in Paris. The large pyramid serves as the main entrance to the Louvre Museum. Completed in 1989, it has become a landmark of the city of Paris. - wikipedia #louvre #paris #france #louvremuseum #museedulouvre #travel #museum #art #louvrepyramid #photography #europe #parisjetaime #parisfrance #toureiffel #photooftheday #eiffeltower #architecture #travelphotography #visitparis #parismonamour #love #summer #monalisa #louvreparis #instaparis #lelouvre #arcdetriomphe #painting #mus #parisatnight

name: 2019-09-17 11.33.33 2134628876139376836_museedulouvre.jpg
text: Amar amarillo y verde soñar✨Una noche (como muchas tantas) soñé colores, en especial éste color verde. Primero quería hacerme unos girasoles que duraran, que conservarán sus pétalos tan amarillos desde el primer día y sus hojas brillarán en un tono verde más fuerte.Unos girasoles que lo único que secará fuera la pintura en ellos🌻Cuando el verde del fondo llegó a mi sueño era así, verdecitos con esa peculiar textura, eran verdes por doquier, era un verde que esa noche me llenó de energía y al despertar estaba bastante feliz. Con ansias y enormes ganas de sacar la pintura de sus frascos comencé a pintar, pintar y pintar 💚 pinté tantos verdes hasta que encontré el soñado✨Y nacieron mis girasoles en un verde de ensueño🌻 Coleccionista de hojas #LifeMH .....#Coleccionistadehojas #arte #xalapa #mexico #acrilico #oleo #artoftheday #lover #girasoles #amantesalosgirasoles #vincentvangogh #vangogh #vangoghart #artemexicano #mexicanartist #verdementa #greenland #artist #acrylicpainting #painting #paintpaintpaint #pinturaacrilica #pinturas  #mexicanartisan #artesanal  #art #artistsoninstagram #artoftheday #museevangogh #museedulouvre

name: 2019-09-17 12.10.48 2134647628495765278_museedulouvre.jpg
text: While I’m feeling really nostalgic for France, I wanted to post this photo. This cellist was busking in one of the passages of the Louvre. When I got within earshot he was playing one of the Bach cello suites, and playing it well. He had some notes in English in his case. They were sweet and joking, talking about how he would use the money to feed his cats. He said he couldn’t say thank you while he played, but he was happy to give out smiles. He also encouraged people to take a minute to really stop and listen, not to just hurry by. I’m great at being busy and I’m always in a hurry -a failing of mine-so I stood there and listened. After the Bach he started playing La Vie en Rose. For a second it seemed trite and a bit pandering to tourists, but he played it so well I got into it and stayed through the whole piece. When he finished, I gave him all my change, which was a lot, and got a smile in return. I don’t know what that music did to me, but I went into the courtyard of the Louvre, stood next to one of the smaller pyramids, and absolutely bawled my eyes out. It was a torrent of emotion that I really didn’t understand, but after a few minutes I felt better. I have no idea who you were, but thank you mystery cellist. You touched  me deeply with your music that day, and I’ll never forget it. #music #museedulouvre

text: Almost every single photo @criskinoflo took of me, was photobombed. As you can see in the photo above, the Louvre Museum photobombed hard. name: 2019-09-17 16.48.43 2134787500982539226_museedulouvre.jpg
text: Spårvagnen (c.1943).🎨 Painted by Olle Olsson.Born: 12 July 1904, Hagalund, Solna, Sweden.Died: 13 June 1972, Hagalund, Solna, Sweden..🖼 Oil on canvas 85 x 90 cm..📝 Olle Olsson-Hagalund is one of Sweden's most appreciated naive artists during the twentieth century. The village Hagalund, Olle Olsson's main source of inspiration, is gone. However his own house and three others still stand which.Olle Olsson Hagalund's naive dreamlike imagery lost some of its popularity during the 60' and 70'. Progressive artistic trends which often involved some political statement lead the art community in Sweden during these two decades. Today however we have rediscovered how timeless the artist was in expressing a blend of dramatic humour with quiet melancholy in a simple lifestyle. Perhaps this technocratic society we live in needs now more than ever his sensitive and loving relationship to relics from the past and his talent for narrative art. As an artist he will always invigorate us with his vibrant array of colours and the intrinsic value of his artistic talents.As a child Olle Olsson was a loner. He often wandered by himself contemplating - observing his surroundings - and drawing. After school, Olle sought employmet at The National Railway Company. He was later dismissed when the company introduced a rationalization program and with small savings in his pocket he registered at the Carl Wilhelmssons Painting School. He spent only a short time at the school. Olle Olsson felt uneasy in the company of colourfull and expressive painters. He began to doubt his competence and was not very disappointed when lack of money forced him to leave. During the following years, Olle Olssonhad long periods of unemployment. He painted in secrecy and did not show his art to anyone.In 1943 the PUB department store organized a competition for young painters. Olle Olsson sent in six paintings of which all were accepted.The critics praised his colouristic talent and ability to bring to life the shabby suburbs in Hagalund.The artist's private life was spent quietly in Hagalund with his wife Maja, whom he married in 1937, and his daughter Lena who was born in 1950....

text: .[📍Le Louvre méconnu / La salle des icônes grecques et russes] _Au premier étage de l’aile de Flore, en fond de Grande Galerie, sont exposées les icônes grecques et russes, noyées dans les collections de peintures espagnoles. Rares sont ceux qui parviennent jusqu’à l’intimiste écrin que constitue la salle 734. Y sont visibles des chefs-d’œuvre, à commencer par la célèbre Vierge géorgienne.____________Ici /Les Apôtres Pierre et Paul Peintre crétoisseconde moitié du XVIe siècle_🕰Les apôtres Pierre et Paul soutiennent un édifice à coupole, figuration symbolique de l'Eglise universelle, instituée par le Christ, dont ils sont les piliers____________Aile Denon1er étage Salle 734____________📷©️InsideTheLouvre / @n.bousser ____________l#ouvre #museedulouvre #louvremuseum #art #culture #painting #icône #vierge #viergegéorgienne #russie #grèce #portrait #paris #france #france🇫🇷 #greek #work #insta #instagram #instatravel #instatrip #travel #trip #instatraveling #patrimoine #chefdoeuvre

text: #旅する日本語 #万福 自分がここに居るのが不思議だった。まさか、人生の中で、ルーブル美術館を訪れるとは思っていもいなかった。美術の授業は好きであったが、世界の名だたる芸術作品について知識も持ち合わせていない人間が、その作品が持つ意味を理解出来るのかも疑問だった。しかし、さすが世に名を轟かせる作品達である。教科書の中の世界でしかなった作品を目の当たりにすると、作品の持つ圧倒的な力に心を奪われてしまった。遥か昔の時代から、ずっとこの作品達は息をしてきたのだ。そして今もなお、私達の前で、褪せることのない輝きを放っている。それを実際目にすることができる機会は、誰もの人生中で必ずあるとは限らない。それは、私にとって思いがけず訪れた幸運であった。ここは、大いなる幸福を味合うことができる場所である。その事実を、遡ること数十分前、ルーブル美術館への入り口を探して彷徨っていた私は知るよしもなかった。#france #francetrip #paris #paristrip #trip #travel #instatravel #tavelgram #igtravel #landscape #townscape #travelphotgraph #louvre #museedulouvre #フランス #フランス旅行 #旅行 #旅行記 #🇫🇷 #20190503#日本だろうと世界だろうとworldwideで道に迷う

name: 2019-09-17 23.23.03 2134985977175965829_museedulouvre.jpg
text: 🇨🇵 Même en admirant les oeuvres rapidement, vous prendriez 4 jours sans dormir pour connaître tout le musée. 😱😳De quel musée parlons-nous? Du Louvre à Paris, où se trouve la merveilleuse Mona Lisa... mais pas que. Le musée a beaucoup plus d'oeuvres et expositions à offrir. 🎨🖼D'ailleurs, le peintre du Ceará (région du Nordeste brésilien) @rinaldobetaj va présenter son exposition "quântico", dans le musée le plus célèbre du monde.Afin de réaliser son rêve, l'artiste a commencé une campagne de financement collectif pour couvrir ses frais de voyage.Faisons honneur à cet artiste - connaissons son travail et aidons-le à porter le nom du Brésil dans d'autres pays. 🌎--------------------🇧🇷 Mesmo observando as obras rapidamente, você demoraria 4 dias sem dormir para conhecer o museu todo. 😱😳De que museu estamos falando? Do Louvre em Paris, onde fica a maravilhosa Mona Lisa... porém, o museu tem muito mais obras e exposições para oferecer. 🎨🖼Inclusive, o pintor cearense @rinaldobetaj vai apresentar sua exposição "quântico", no museu de arte mais famoso do mundo.A fim de realizar seu sonho, o artista deu início a uma campanha de financiamento coletivo para cobrir os gastos desta viagem.Vamos prestigiar o artista, conhecer seu trabalho e ajudá-lo a levar o nome do Brasil para outros países.🌎 Fonte e foto : https://www.opovo.com.br/noticias/fortaleza/2019/08/23/pintor-cearense-realiza-financiamento-coletivo-para-expor-obras-no-museu-do-louvre--em-paris.html

text: Some say, if you didn't pay attention to the artwork, it would take you just 5 hours to walk the 14.5 km (9 miles) of corridors in the Louvre. But if you stop for just 10 seconds to see each of the 35,000 artworks exhibited (out of the approximately 460,000 that the museum retains), you will need 3 days and two nights non-stop..No idea if the math works out but one thing I do know is...it's a BIG place...an absolutely magnificent place...with a lot to see! 👀.. #museedulouvre #louvre #louvremuseum #museum #history #art #artcollective #paintings #artifacts #fountain #pyramid #glasspyramid #amazingarchitecture #archidaily #building_shotz #hello_france #topfrancephoto #parislife #parisjetaime #thisisparis #topparisphoto #paris #france 🇫🇷#photographer#photography #architecture #architecturephotography#canonphotography#canonphotographers

name: 2019-09-18 07.29.24 2135230760943722175_museedulouvre.jpg
text: "Aux femmes assassinées, la patrie indifférente". Samedi nous étions une trentaine de militantes à nous rendre au Louvre pour rappeler à Emmanuel Macron ses engagements sur les lieux mêmes du discours de son investiture. Alors que la lutte contre les violences faites aux femmes devait faire partie intégrante de la grande cause du quinquennat, où en sommes-nous aujourd'hui? L'année 2019 ne s'est même pas encore entièrement écoulée que nous en sommes déjà à 106 féminicides, un grenelle et trop peu de mesures concrètes mises en place pour le moment ni assez d'argent posé sur la table. Nous sommes pourtant nombreuses et nombreux à proposer régulièrement des actions à mettre en place pour éradiquer sur le long terme les violences faites aux femmes. Sachez que de belles paroles ne suffisent plus à masquer votre inaction et que nous n'arrêterons pas tant que nous n'aurons pas obtenu ce que nous sommes venues chercher.______________ Merci infiniment à @marguerite_stern et @sofia_sept7 pour leur militantisme perpétuel et acharné. Je pense aussi à toi @rudykantfail , mon acolyte de la nuit, et à toutes les autres héroïnes qui n'ont pas peur d'élever leur voix dans le silence imposé par l'oppression. #ensembleonvaincra______________Si vous êtes sur Paris, rejoignez le mouvement ici @collages_feminicides_paris (MP si vous voulez coller).Sinon tapez dans la barre de recherches "collages_feminicides_"le nom de votre ville". Si votre ville n'y est pas, n'hésitez pas à créer vous-mêmes une page et à nous en informer pour qu'on relaie l'information. _____________1ère, 2ème, 5ème, 6ième 📸 @paulinemakoveitchoux3ème, 4ème 📸 @eliseveillardgotchac_____________#revolutionfeministe #stopfeminicide #iamnext #niunamenos #eminebulut #ellesnousmanquent #grenellecontrelesviolencesconjugales #jesuisfeminicidophobe #feminist #feminism #collage #collagesfeminicides  #museedulouvre #onveutunmilliard

name: 2019-09-18 17.55.53 2135546080279214632_museedulouvre.jpg
text: Apolo vence Píton (Eugène Delacroix, 1850-1851, óleo sobre tela, 800x750cm, Galeria de Apolo, Museu do Louvre, Paris)Delacroix recebeu a encomenda desta obra em 1850, após um decreto que destinou 12 milhões de francos para a recuperação da Galeria de Apolo. Elaborou o esboço e numerosos estudos, sendo um trabalho longo e fatigante para a saúde já debilitada do pintor. Pierre Andrieu, seu aluno, colaborou na realização desta obra.A composição retrata a luta entre Apolo e Píton (a serpente filho da deusa Gaia), representando alegoricamente o encontro entre a luz e a escuridão, a inteligência e a força obscura da irracionalidade. Apolo, na carruagem, já lançou uma de suas flechas, enquanto Ártemis, sua irmã, lhe oferece sua aljava. O monstro, já ferido, se contorce.Apolo era considerado o deus do Sol, das artes e poesia. Portanto, sua ligação com o Rei Luís XIV, o Rei Sol, faz todo o sentido. Este monarca encomendou a decoração da Galeria de Apolo antes da família real deixar o Louvre em direção a Versalhes. O local foi originalmente chamado de Pequena Galeria e é decorado com alto relevos e diversas pinturas, além de pátina em folhas de ouro.Bibliografia:Grandes Mestres: Delacroix. name: 2019-09-18 20.20.55 2135619081931626026_museedulouvre.jpg
text: My audio guide wasn’t wrong when it said that the first glimpse of Nike, from across the corridor will take your breath away. The Winged Victory of Samothrace - Nike, the Greek goddess of victory is one of the most celebrated sculptures in the world. She conveys a sense of action and triumph as well as portraying artful flowing drapery, as though the goddess were descending to alight upon the prow of a ship. The work is notable for its convincing rendering of a pose where violent motion and sudden stillness meet, for its graceful balance and for the rendering of the figure's draped garments, compellingly depicted as if rippling in a strong sea breeze. I stood for so many minutes amazed at how sculptors in 2nd century BC could create this level of motion and transparency in marble. Look at how the fabric appears to cling to her waist as though it’s slightly wet. You can almost see that it was some kind of sheer fabric. What happened to her head? What does she look like? Where was she first standing? What was it like when she was unveiled for the first time? Who worshipped her?

name: 2019-09-19 00.37.38 2135748293907551553_museedulouvre.jpg
text: Ned Osborne on 'Grey Tick', Zennor Hill, Cornwall..🎨 Painted by Sir Alfred James Munnings.Born: 8 October 1878, Mendham, Suffolk, England.Died: 17 July 1959, Dedham, Essex, England. (aged 80).🖼 Oil on canvas 63,5 x 76,2 cm..📝 Showing some early talent, Munnings was apprenticed to a firm of lithographers, Page Brothers in Norwich for six years, studying at Norwich School of Art in the evening.He had some success locally and showed two paintings at the Royal Academy in 1899. In the same year he returned to set up his studio in Mendham, and in an accident lost the sight in one eye.In his early years he supplemented his income by designing posters at which, with is consummate draughtsmanship he excelled. He studied briefly in Paris between 1902 and 1903.Munnings drew his subject matter from the East Anglian landscape and rural society. A horse fair of 1901 showed an early interest in horses while fairgrounds and rural occupations provided the artist with considerable subject matter.1910 saw Munnings visit Lamorna in Cornwall where he met Laura and Harold Knight, lifelong friends, and where he stayed between 1911 and 1916.In 1913 he held his first one-man show at the Leicester Galleries, where Laura Knight showed.In 1918 Munnings was appointed as a war artist with the Canadian Cavalry Brigade, producing an important body of work for the Canadian Government.Munnings settled in Dedham in 1918, marrying Violet in 1920. He was elected Royal Academician in 1925.In 1944 Munnings was knighted and elected President of the Royal Academy between 1944 and 1949. In this latter role he famously made known his utter contempt for ‘Modern Art’. Munnings was a prolific artist and a consummate draughtsman, whose work as a war artist raised his profile and reputation.Best known for his equestrian works, portraits and racing works, Munnings range was enormous. He excelled in landscape and scenes of rural life, recording a way of life that was coming to an end.His works can be found in museums in: Birmingham; Liverpool; London, Tate Gallery; Norwich; Preston; USA, Yale University; Brisbane and Melbourne..(Fig 2, 3, 4: Details)...

name: 2019-09-19 03.26.02 2135833044704076680_museedulouvre.jpg
text: 🤔Як потрапити в Лувр без черги?.👌🏻Все просто - не йдіть через головний вхід, тобто піраміди. Напишу про той, яким вийшло скористатися..🆓Якщо ви плануєте прийти у день, коли вхід безкоштовний, то це дещо складніше, але також реально..☝🏻Нам вдалося це зробити завдяки тому, що попередньо ми зайшли у п`ятницю пізно ввечері і взяли друковану 🗺 карту музею. Вхід у цей день після 18 також безкоштовний, але часу щось роздивлятися вже не було..☺️Тому у неділю ми прийшли до одного з входів, а саме до входу для тих, у кого вже є квитки (позначив його на фото)..📍Він знаходиться навпроти Піраміди, в проході, що веде до палацу Пале-Рояль (напрямок до вулиці Ріволі). В цьому випадку ви потрапите безпосередньо в музей, не проходячи через підземний зал з касами.🤷🏻‍♂️Без квитка зазвичай там не пропустять, але на щастя у мене в руках була карта, і охоронець подумав, що ми вже були в середині, ненароком вийшли і хочемо зайти ще раз..😅P.S. На жаль, не всі охоронці розуміють англійську, тому дуже добре, якщо з вами буде хтось, хто хоча б на базовому рівні спілкується французькою..👇🏻Якщо маєте ще питання, то пишіть.... #savkinsonontour #travellifehacks #cheaptrip #cheaptravel #дешевіподорожі #бюджетніподорожі #бюджетнітури #тревел #тревелблог #подорожі #подорож #авторськіподорожі #лувр #париж #париж2019 #louvre #paris #museedulouvre

name: 2019-09-19 04.13.22 2135856873567027524_museedulouvre.jpg
text: Louvre com bebê, dá? Dá sim!O museu é muito acessível a carrinho de bebês, tem trocador, lanchonete e espaços pra sentar, amamentar, dar comidinha.Algumas passagens entre uma sala e outra tem alguns degraus, aí tem que carregar o carrinho no braço mesmo, mas são poucas e muitas tem rampas ou elevadores pra cadeirantes que podem ser usado por carrinho de bebê. Aliás, quem tem criança de colo e carrinho geralmente tem atendimento preferencial, junto com grávidas, idosos e PNEs. Quando os pequenos se enjoarem, é bom deixar eles andarem um pouco, brincar pelo chão. Respeitar horários de soneca e alimentação, trocar fraldas. Eles aproveitam do jeito deles e nós, do jeito que dá! Planejamento é tudo... selecione as obras imperdíveis e foco nelas. O que vier a mais é lucro.#paris #france #travelwithkids #pariswithkids #instagood #travelingwithkids #kidsandtravel #travelgram #instatravel #viagemcomcriancas #viajandocombebe #viajandocomcrianças #viajandocomcriancas #viagemcombebe #louvre #louvremuseum #museedulouvre

text: Lightness Strength🕊Acho incrível a escultura “Victoire de Samothrace”! Esculpida 200 a.C representa a deusa grega Nice e é um dos principais destaques no Museu do Louvre 🌬mesmo incompleta, é considerada uma das grandes obras do período helenístico pela leveza e movimento de suas asas e drapeado, parece voar suavemente cortando o vento com determinação e força.🌬 Ótima inspiração... tem como não amar?! #arte #museedulouvre #sculpture #goddesses #artinspiration #millencurates

name: 2019-09-19 05.24.50 2135892846653561910_museedulouvre.jpg
text: Salve, sono Nike, fino al IV secolo a.C. non avevo identità, anzi, ero spesso associata ad Athena, dea della Sapienza, delle Arti, della tessitura e delle strategie militari, ma dal III a.C. si cominciò a narrare fossi figlia di Pallade, che altri chiamano Pallante, ovvero il Titano che si unì con la ninfa Stige e da cui nacqui. Per fortuna non sono figlia unica, ho tre fratelli Cratos, personificazione della Potenza, Zelo, della costanza e la gelosia, e Bia, la violenza.Infine ci sono io, Vittoria, “Nike” in greco, in qualità di messaggera della vittoria sportiva e bellica.Il mio autore è ignoto, nonostante oggi molti ritengano che a realizzarmi fu lo scultore ellenistico Pitocrito, poiché al momento della mia scoperta sull’isola di Samotracia venne rinvenuto nei pressi un basamento che riportava il suo nome#nikedisamotracia #museedulouvre

text: When I realize where I am in my journey as a writer, when I realize how little I have done, sometimes I feel overwhelmed. ..A walk through the greatest museum in the world helped it sink in how small I am. How much work it takes to create something that will outlive me. How God created us in His image so that we can make things like Him, but—like Van Gogh—we might never become famous in our lifetimes. Our names might not be known until long after we are gone. ..Still, we must keep creating, must keep on dreaming. The #Louvre is a gift, and it only exists because these artists kept creating...though they did not know.......#museedulouvre #parisfrance #igartists #igwriters #igpoets #parisfrance #mybeautifulparis #catholiclife #catholicwoman #vscocam #bookstagram

text: A little late-night beauty for the late-night scrollers.....Crop of “Les Trois Grâces” by Jean-Baptiste Regnault (1793-94)..This 18th century painting depicts three #goddesses from ancient Greek mythology called the Graces. They came to be considered as companions of Aphrodite, the goddess of Love and Beauty. According to poetic and literary tradition they represented charm, beauty, and human creativity. ..This painting, with its smooth contours, sinuous forms, and luminous colors is typical of Regnault's style. The contrast of light and shade and the pure "Greek style" lines reflect Regnault's charming brand of #neoclassicsim, expressed with almost excessive perfection...#museedulouvre #parisfrance #regnault #lestroisgraces #thethreegraces #euphrosyne #thalia #aglaia #greekmythology #thecharites #aphrodite #venus #18thcenturyfrance #sullywing #arthistory #naturalbeauty

text: Marie Bashkirtseff, Woman with cigarette, in the artist's studio. From Russia, she studied in Paris, at the Academie Julian, where women could learn how to paint the nude model. She published articles in feminist gazettes under the name of Pauline Orrell. In her Journal, she expressed the difficult condition of women artists in a male-dominated environment and she struggled against this. She exhibited naturalist paintings in the Paris Salon between 1880 and 1884. Her career was cut short by tuberculosis and she died at the age of 24, in 1884.#womenartists#drawing#graphitepencils#papercraft#artiststudios#artdaily#dailyart#museeorsay#artsgraphiques#bashkirtseff#19thcenturyart

name: 2019-09-19 13.54.42 2136149471577416515_museedulouvre.jpg
text: Нет на свете человека, достигшего совершеннолетнего возраста, который бы не знал, что такое Лувр. Musee du Louvre - самый известный музей в мире 🌍. Люди из всех стран приезжают сюда, чтобы посмотреть эту громадную галерею🖼. Из этих соображений, можно понять, что каждый день в этом месте просто безумное количество народу, а значит громадные очереди...Как сэкономить своё время и не заблудиться в Лувре?Опять-таки, важно купить билеты онлайн, но на такой огромный музей этого не будет достаточно. Очень рекомендуется взять с собой гида по Лувр. Сайтов с услугами экскурсии по этому музею огромное количество, на абсолютно разных языках. Как говориться: любой каприз за ваши деньги 💶. Но гид, действительно, нужен. Он может провести вас в музей без очередей, показать основные залы, рассказать главную информацию и помочь не заблудиться среди бесчисленного количества залов. Важный момент, если вы решили взять экскурсию в Лувр, спросите: даёт ли гид наушник 🎧 , для более комфортного проведения экскурсия !!! Это нужно, чтобы во время экскурсии вы могли подходит к картинам и смотреть интересующие вас детали. Мы про наушники не спросили, рассчитывая, что в подобных музеях данное само собой разумеется, что было некой ошибкой. Из-за гула огромного народа людей со всех сторон, слушать экскурсию без наушника было не очень удобно.Лувр - это то место, которое нужно посетить хотя бы раз в жизни, если вы были в Париже. Главный музей в мире, все ж таки.#пропариж #пролувр #paris #museelouvre #museedulouvre #🇫🇷

text: The Louvre is the world's largest museum and houses one of the most impressive art collections in history. The magnificent, baroque-style palace and museum — LeMusée du Louvre in French — sits along the banks of the Seine River in Paris. It is one of the city's biggest tourist attractions.History of the LouvreThe Louvre was originally built as a fortress in 1190, but was reconstructed in the 16th century to serve as a royal palace. "Like many buildings, it was built and rebuilt over the years," said Tea Gudek Snajdar, an Amsterdam-based art historian, museum docent and a blogger at Culture Tourist. name: 2019-09-19 14.53.23 2136179008168129519_museedulouvre.jpg
text: Self-Portrait as a Lute Player (c.1615 - 17).🎨 Painted by Artemisia Gentileschi.Born: 8 July 1593, Rome, Italy.Died: 1653, Naples, Italy..🖼 Oil on canvas 77,5 × 71,8 cm..🏛 Location: Wadsworth Atheneum Museum of Art..📝 Her father was the Tuscan master Orazio Gentileschi. She and her brothers received their first artistic lessons in their father's workshop. It soon became clear that Artemisia was much more talented than her brothers.She made her first well-known work at the age of 17: Susanna and the Elders. Some think that Artemisia had been harrassed just like Susanna, and that she used that experience in the painting.Being a girl she was not accepted into any painting academy. Her father then had a colleague give her further lessons. This Agostino Tassi not only taught her painting but raped her as well. When that became public Tassi was sent to jail for a year.Artemisia's father quickly arranged a marriage, in order to save his daughter's honour. She married Pierantonio Stiattesi. The couple moved to Florence, where Gentileschi became a celebrated artist. She was accepted into a painters' academy, befriended Galileo Galilei and was protected by the powerful de' Medici family.In 1621 Artemisia Gentileschi moved back to Rome. She probably also spent some time in Venice between 1627 and 1630. This was not a very successful decade.Just like Caravaggio, who still had much influence at the time, Gentileschi moved to Naples, in 1630. She also worked in England for a while, beginning in 1638. Her father had a position at the court of Charles I. Some time after his death in 1639 she returned to Naples, where she was to work for the remainder of her life.It is not known exactly when she died. It is thought that she was one of many victims of the great pestilence that struck Naples in 1656.Her father was heavily influenced by the baroque master Caravaggio, and so was the young Artemisia. She is considered to be one of his most talented followers. Later she added classical influences into her work..(Fig 2, 3, 4: Details)...

name: 2019-09-19 18.17.02 2136281507439037122_museedulouvre.jpg
text: Théodore Géricault 's The Raft of The Medusa (Le Radeau de la Méduse) is 200 years old. Or 201 since it was painted between 1818–1819. It was completed when Géricault  was 27 and shown for the first time in the 1819 Paris Salon.This gigantic painting 4.91m × 7.16m (16' 1" × 23' 6" )with larger than life-size figures hangs in the Louvre and depicts what followed after the French frigate Méduse ran on a sandbank off the West African coast on 2 July 1816.The Méduse had a shortage of lifeboats and a raft for 150 people was built. After 13 days adrift, only15 people survived  death, thirst, hunger, cannibalism. The painting shows the moment when the survivors saw the  Argus, a ship that found them by chance. 2 centuries ago The Raft of The Medusa with its brutal display of the reality of 13 days at sea without food or water garned both praise and criticism. This Caravaggesque  masterpiece - the mastery of chiaroscuro is worthy of Caravaggio - is a landmark of 19th century painting and become one of the most relevalt painting in the History of Art and Painting. Géricault himself is inserted in the picture - the figure face down, with his arm stretched. In 1985 The Pogues used a painting by Peter Mennim based on The Raft of the Medusa, as the cover of Rum Sodomy & the Lash, their second album. In the album cover the band members' faces replace those of the men on the raft.#théodoregéricault #théodoregéricault #gèricault #gericault  #leradeaudelameduse  #theraftofthemedusa #oiloncanvas  #frenchromanticism #chiaroscuro #oiloncanvas #louvre #museedulouvre #museedulouvreparis  #art #painting #salon #1819parissalon #19thcenturyart #romanticism #frenchart #louvrepaintings #historyofart #arthistory #thepogues #rumsodomyandthelash #petermennim #albumcovers #music #musicandart

text: 131/365- here she goes again, coming at you with all the late posts. PARIS day 2- the louvre. This place is huge!! But so beautiful. So amazing to be surrounded by so much art and history. Found out from a tour guide that the louvre only show cases 20% of the art that it houses. 80% is in storage. That’s mind blowing considering how much there is to see. She said that if you were stand in front of every art piece that is showcased for two minutes, it would take you 10 months to see everything and that’s without sleep 😮 definitely a place to visit every time! More louvre to come 😁 #museedulouvre #thelouvre #paris #france #solotravel #worldtraveler

text: J'ai très peu de photo à l'heure bleue.Pour ceux qui ne le savent pas, c'est ce moment juste après le coucher de soleil où le ciel est encore lumineux et est, comme son nom l'indique, bleu.On voit sur ma photo que le soleil illumine encore bien le côté gauche, ce qui permet de palier au manque d'un élément alors qu'à droite une aile du musée est sur la photo.I have very little amount of pictures taken at the blue hour.For those who do not know it, it is this moment just after sunset where the sky is still bright and is, as its name suggests, blue.We see in my picture that the sun still brightens the left side, which helps to overcome the lack of an element while to the right a part of the museum is on the photo.#louvre #louvremuseum #louvrepyramid #lelouvre #museedulouvre #louvreparis #parisismoveablefeast #parisiloveyou #heurebleue #bluehour #loves_paris_ #longexposure #longexpo #longueexposition #bestplacetobe #Reflection_gram #reflection_shotz #reflection_shots #reflection #reflet

She was considered as a canon and the most beautiful woman of the kingdom until she was replaced by her older sister from Milo.But wait ! It isn't over ! We she was found and given to the king by the city of Arles her arms were missing, a sculptor named Girardon restored her but most of his work became criticized for changes from the other examples we had, he made her a Venus while the city saw her as Diane (Artemis)#artemis #arttrivia #trivia #Venus #venusdarles #paris #museum #museedulouvre #louvre #artwork #sculpture #statue #ink #pen #dotwork #artworknow #abtcamp #antiquity #woman #artist #sketch #sketchbook #usk #urbansketch @museelouvre @uskparis @museedulouvre9 #blackwork

name: 2019-09-20 01.15.05 2136491916720367477_museedulouvre.jpg
text: Michelangelo Buonarroti, The Dying Slave, 1513-16, marble, 215 cm, Musée du Louvre, Paris. Michelangelo Buonarroti, 1475-1564, was an Italian Renaissance sculptor, painter, architect, and poet who had a major influence on the development of Western art. The frescoes on the ceiling of the Sistine Chapel are probably the best known of his works today, the artist however thought of himself primarily as a sculptor. Michelangelo worked in marble sculpture all his life and in the other arts, painting for exemple, only during certain periods. In his quest for absolute truth, he abandoned a sculpture when he felt he could not attain his ideal. He left the marks of his tools clearly visible on them. Michelangelo worked relentlessly in his quest to liberate the figure imprisoned within and became an expert in portraying the human body. Because of his ability to depict an unparalleled variety of movements, emotions and postures, Michelangelo was acknowledged to be not only equalling the masters of classical antiquity but also surpassing them. This sculpture is one of six ‘slaves’ executed by Michelangelo for the tomb of Pope Julius II. This figure, together with the Rebellious Slave, was executed for the second project for the tomb. The bonds around his chest indicate his captive state. Michelangelo planned to place them on either side of the Moses. The iconographical theme is something of a mystery. Historians are not in agreement about what these captive figures symbolize. The dying young man evokes a certain sensuality in his posture. It has caused doubts if the figure is a dying slave at all. The second project in the end was never completed in this form.Check out my new account @art_questions_and_debates and @my_favorite_work_of_art#michelangelobuonarroti #thedyingslave #louvre #michelangelo #dyingslave #arthistorian #artblog #museedulouvre #sculpture #muséedulouvre #louvre #sculptures #sculptor #renaissance #marble #marbleart #marblesculpture

name: 2019-09-20 03.44.47 2136567261326252920_museedulouvre.jpg
text: 🇫🇷 El Museo del Louvre es uno de los museos más importantes del mundo y el más grande de París, con una superficie de 210.000 m² de los cuales 68.000 están consagrados a exposiciones. Está situado en el centro de la ciudad, entre la orilla derecha del río Sena y una de las calles más concurridas de la ciudad : la calle Rivoli, en el distrito primero.El edificio es de una gran belleza y constituye un atractivo en sí mismo. Se podría visitar el Louvre únicamente para admirar este antiguo palacio real : el Palacio del Louvre,  que constituye un vasto conjunto de construcciones monumentales cuya historia se remonta a 1546 a nuestros días. 🇫🇷 .. 👉🏼𝒯𝒾𝓅𝓈 𝒹𝑒 ℛ𝑒𝓁𝒶𝒿𝒶𝓉𝑒 𝓅𝒶𝑒𝒶 𝓋𝒾𝓈𝒾𝓉𝒶𝓇 𝑒𝓈𝓉𝑒 𝑔𝓇𝒶𝓃 𝓂𝓊𝓈𝑒𝑜! •ENTRADAS-Los primeros domingos de cada mes entre Octubre y Marzo el museo es completamente gratis para todo el mundo. -Los viernes a partir de las 6 de la tarde si tenes menos de 26 años es gratis.-El boleto de entrada cuesta 17 euros por adulto aprox-Evita ʟᴀ ᴇɴᴛʀᴀᴅᴀ ᴅᴇ ʟᴀ ᴘɪʀᴀᴍɪᴅᴇ! Es la entrada principal al museo y la mayoria de los turistas se juntan ahi, poca gente sabe que hay otras entradas al museo. .📍Consultanos por paquetes a Europa disponibles y acorde a tu comodidad y gustos!.....#francés #francia #europa #europe_pics #amazing_shots #museo #museedulouvre #picoftheday #viajaresvivir #relajateviajes #modoselfie

name: 2019-09-20 05.01.10 2136605711373842494_museedulouvre.jpg
text: ⠀ ⠀ ⠀ ⠀ ⠀ ⠀ ⠀ ⠀ ⠀ ⠀ ⠀ ⠀ Tesoro: 👉 La Belle Ferroniere - 1495 d.C.Artista: 🇮🇹 Leonardo Da Vinci Luogo:📍#Parigi - Museo del #LouvreFoto: 📸@museelouvre Tag: 🔑#tesori_italianiFamily:👉 @europe_treasures👉 @contemporary_treasures👉 @archaeology.treasures✤ ✤ ✤🇮🇹 La Belle Ferronnière è un dipinto a olio su tavola (63x45 cm) di Leonardo Da Vinci, databile al 1490-1495 circa e conservato al Louvre di Parigi. Il nome del dipinto, ossia “la bella moglie di un mercante di ferramenta”, è dovuto a un errore di catalogazione del XVIII secolo: "Ferronnière" si riferisce infatti alla catenella con gioiello che le cinge la fronte, ornamento tipico dell'epoca che prese il nome da Madame Ferron, amante di Francesco I di Francia. Il ritratto mostra la fanciulla a mezzobusto, su sfondo scuro e dietro un parapetto alla fiamminga, dal volto rivolto allo spettatore ma dallo sguardo sfuggente. Il contatto visivo non stabilito ne accentua così il senso di enigmatica inaccessibilità.✤ ✤ ✤🇬🇧 Belle Ferronnière is an oil painting on panel (63x45 cm) portrait of a lady, usually attributed to Leonardo da Vinci. It dates to to 1490-1495 and is housed at the Louvre in Paris. The painting's title, meaning “the beautiful wife of an ironmonger", is due to a cataloging mistake of the eighteenth century: "Ferronnière" refers in fact to the chain with jewel that straddles her forehead, a typical ornament of the era named after Madame Ferron, mistress of King Francis I of France. The portrait shows the girl half-body, on a dark background and behind a parapet in the Flemish style, facing the spectator while looking away. The elusive look increases the feeling of an enigmatic and distant figure.✤ ✤ ✤#beniculturali #italia #beniculturali30 #italy #cultura #arte #labelleferroniere #musee #artwork #pittura #storia #museedulouvre #italianart #volgoarte #culturalheritage #masterpiece #italianart #abudhabi #traveling_arte #leonardodavinci #louvremuseum #artista #pinacoteca #leonardo #paris #storiadellarte
